{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ELn8ysXCygDChS1N4gCgEs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Implementation History — 300-referral-system\n     2→\n     3→Iteration log for the autonomous spec loop. Each entry records what was\n     4→attempted and whether it succeeded. The agent reads this file at the start\n     5→of every iteration to understand prior context.\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## Iteration 1 — 2026-03-24T21:27:27Z — OK\n    10→\n    11→**Item**: [backend] Database migration `011_referral.sql`\n    12→**Status**: Done\n    13→**Changes**:\n    14→- Created `services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql` with all 5 referral tables:\n    15→  - `referral_codes` — one code per wallet (UNIQUE on wallet + code)\n    16→  - `referral_links` — immutable referrer binding (UNIQUE on referee_wallet)\n    17→  - `referral_earnings` — per-game earnings with idempotency guard (UNIQUE on referee_wallet + round_id)\n    18→  - `referral_claims` — async payout tracking with status CHECK constraint (pending/processing/completed/failed)\n    19→  - `referral_kol_rates` — KOL custom rates (wallet PK)\n    20→- Indexes: referrer/referee wallet lookups on earnings, round_id, claims by wallet+date, partial index on pending/processing claims, referrer_wallet on links\n    21→- Follows existing migration patterns (IF NOT EXISTS, TIMESTAMPTZ, BIGINT for lamports, no foreign keys)\n    22→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18 tasks)\n    23→**Note**: Agent falsely claimed DONE after this single item. Loop accepted it (no guard).\n    24→\n    25→## Gap Analysis — 2026-03-24T21:41:16Z\n    26→- **Result**: Gap analysis report generated\n    27→- **Report**: gap-analysis.md\n    28→- **Log**: gap-analysis.log\n    29→\n    30→## Iteration 2 — 2026-03-25T08:54:27Z — FALSE DONE (rejected retroactively)\n    31→- **Agent claimed DONE** but only the migration was complete. Checklist was refined between runs.\n    32→- **Log**: iteration-002.log\n    33→\n    34→## Iteration 3 — 2026-03-25T09:09:19Z — OK\n    35→\n    36→**Item**: [backend] DB client methods in `db.ts`: `insertReferralCode`, `getReferralCodeByWallet`, `getReferralCodeByCode`, `upsertReferralCode` for code CRUD\n    37→**Status**: Done\n    38→**Changes**:\n    39→- Added `ReferralCode` interface to type section (id, wallet, code, created_at, updated_at)\n    40→- Added 4 method signatures to `Db` interface: `insertReferralCode`, `getReferralCodeByWallet`, `getReferralCodeByCode`, `upsertReferralCode`\n    41→- Implemented all 4 methods in `createDb()`:\n    42→  - `insertReferralCode`: INSERT with RETURNING *\n    43→  - `getReferralCodeByWallet`: SELECT by wallet, returns undefined if not found\n    44→  - `getReferralCodeByCode`: SELECT by code, returns undefined if not found\n    45→  - `upsertReferralCode`: INSERT ON CONFLICT (wallet) DO UPDATE — replaces code for existing wallet\n    46→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18 tasks)\n    47→**Note**: Agent falsely claimed DONE after this single item. Loop accepted it (no guard).\n    48→\n    49→## Gap Analysis — 2026-03-25T09:26:04Z\n    50→- **Result**: Gap analysis report updated (post-iteration-3)\n    51→- **Report**: gap-analysis.md\n    52→- **Totals**: 15 SATISFIED, 0 DEFERRED, 75 GAP (90 total criteria)\n    53→\n    54→## Iteration 4 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n    55→\n    56→**Item**: [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralLink`, `getReferralLinkByReferee`, referral link queries\n    57→**Status**: Done\n    58→**Changes**:\n    59→- Added `ReferralLink` interface to type section (id, referrer_wallet, referee_wallet, created_at)\n    60→- Added 3 method signatures to `Db` interface: `insertReferralLink`, `getReferralLinkByReferee`, `getReferralLinksByReferrer`\n    61→- Implemented all 3 methods in `createDb()`:\n    62→  - `insertReferralLink`: INSERT with RETURNING *\n    63→  - `getReferralLinkByReferee`: SELECT by referee_wallet, returns undefined if not found\n    64→  - `getReferralLinksByReferrer`: SELECT all links where wallet is referrer, ordered by created_at DESC\n    65→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18 tasks)\n    66→\n    67→## Fix — 2026-03-25 — Loop signal detection bug\n    68→- **Problem**: Signal detection (`rg` on raw stream-json log) matched tag text inside tool results (files the agent read), not just agent output. History file containing the DONE tag as prose triggered false positive.\n    69→- **Fix**: Signal detection now extracts only assistant text via `jq` before searching for tags. Also added mandatory Checklist Audit step in prompt (agent must enumerate all items before claiming done).\n    70→- **Spec update**: Referral codes changed to always be player-chosen (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`). No auto-generation.\n    71→\n    72→## Iteration 4 — 2026-03-25T10:22:52Z — FALSE DONE (signal detection bug)\n    73→- **Result**: Agent did NOT claim done (said \"29 items remain\"), but script matched DONE tag in history file tool result\n    74→- **Log**: iteration-004.log\n    75→\n    76→## Devnet E2E — 2026-03-25T10:22:57Z\n    77→- **Result**: PASS\n    78→\n    79→## Gap Analysis — 2026-03-25 (post-iteration-4)\n    80→- **Result**: Gap analysis report updated\n    81→- **Report**: gap-analysis.md\n    82→- **Totals**: 17 SATISFIED, 0 DEFERRED, 73 GAP (90 total criteria)\n    83→- **Changes vs previous**: +2 SATISFIED (link CRUD methods: `insertReferralLink`, `getReferralLinkByReferee`, `getReferralLinksByReferrer` added to db.ts; updated evidence for FR-2 criteria 2d, 2f)\n    84→- **Spec FR checkboxes**: Updated with evidence annotations\n    85→\n    86→## Gap Analysis — 2026-03-25T10:43:21Z\n    87→- **Result**: Gap analysis report generated\n    88→- **Report**: gap-analysis.md\n    89→- **Log**: gap-analysis.log\n    90→\n    91→## Iteration 5 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n    92→\n    93→**Item**: [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralEarning`, `getPendingBalance`, `getReferralEarnings`, `getReferralStats`\n    94→**Status**: Done\n    95→**Changes**:\n    96→- Added `ReferralEarning` interface (id, referrer_wallet, referee_wallet, round_id, game_type, wager_lamports, fee_lamports, referrer_earned_lamports, referrer_rate_bps, referee_rebate_lamports, referee_rebate_rate_bps, created_at)\n    97→- Added `ReferralStats` interface (referred_count, active_count, total_volume_lamports, total_earned_lamports, pending_lamports)\n    98→- Added `normalizeReferralEarning()` helper to convert BIGINT columns to JS numbers\n    99→- Added 4 method signatures to `Db` interface + implementations in `createDb()`:\n   100→  - `insertReferralEarning(params)`: INSERT with all earning fields, RETURNING *, normalized\n   101→  - `getPendingBalance(wallet)`: SUM(referrer_earned where referrer) + SUM(referee_rebate where referee) - SUM(completed/pending/processing claims). Returns lamport string\n   102→  - `getReferralEarnings(wallet, page, limit)`: paginated SELECT by referrer_wallet, newest first, with totalPages count\n   103→  - `getReferralStats(wallet)`: single query returning referred_count, active_count (7d), total_volume, total_earned, pending_lamports\n   104→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) — no new errors introduced.\n   105→\n   106→## Iteration 5 — 2026-03-25T11:43:58Z — OK\n   107→- **Log**: iteration-005.log\n   108→\n   109→## Iteration 6 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   110→\n   111→**Item**: [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralClaim`, `getReferralClaim`, `updateClaimStatus`, `getReferrerRate(wallet)`\n   112→**Status**: Done\n   113→**Changes**:\n   114→- Added `ReferralClaim` interface (id, wallet, amount_lamports, status, tx_signature, error, requested_at, processed_at)\n   115→- Added 4 method signatures to `Db` interface + implementations in `createDb()`:\n   116→  - `insertReferralClaim(wallet, amountLamports)`: INSERT with status='pending', RETURNING *\n   117→  - `getReferralClaim(claimId)`: SELECT by UUID id, returns undefined if not found\n   118→  - `updateClaimStatus(claimId, status, meta?)`: UPDATE status + optional tx_signature/error, sets processed_at on completed/failed\n   119→  - `getReferrerRate(wallet, defaultRateBps)`: SELECT from referral_kol_rates, falls back to defaultRateBps param\n   120→- Added `referralDefaultRateBps` and `referralMinClaimLamports` to Config interface + loadConfig() (env vars `REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS` default 1000, `REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS` default 10000000)\n   121→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) — no new errors introduced.\n   122→\n   123→## Iteration 6 — 2026-03-25T11:50:09Z — OK\n   124→- **Log**: iteration-006.log\n   125→\n   126→## Iteration 7 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   127→\n   128→**Item**: [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/code` — set player-chosen code\n   129→**Status**: Done\n   130→**Changes**:\n   131→- Created `services/backend/src/routes/referral.ts` with `createReferralRoutes({ db })` factory\n   132→- Implemented `POST /code` endpoint:\n   133→  - Requires JWT auth (wallet from context)\n   134→  - Validates code format: 3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]` regex\n   135→  - Checks code uniqueness via `db.getReferralCodeByCode()` before upsert\n   136→  - Uses `db.upsertReferralCode(wallet, code)` to set/replace\n   137→  - Returns `{ code, url }` where url is `https://taunt.bet/r/{code}`\n   138→  - Error responses: 400 (invalid body/code format), 409 (code taken), 500 (unexpected)\n   139→  - Handles race condition on duplicate code with catch on constraint violation\n   140→- Follows existing patterns: Hono factory, AppEnv type, logger(message, fields)\n   141→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) — no new errors introduced.\n   142→\n   143→## Iteration 7 — 2026-03-25T11:55:22Z — OK\n   144→- **Log**: iteration-007.log\n   145→\n   146→## Iteration 8 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   147→\n   148→**Item**: [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/code` — return current code for authenticated wallet, or 404\n   149→**Status**: Done\n   150→**Changes**:\n   151→- Added `GET /code` endpoint to `services/backend/src/routes/referral.ts`\n   152→  - Reads wallet from JWT auth context (`c.get(\"wallet\")`)\n   153→  - Calls `db.getReferralCodeByWallet(wallet)` to look up existing code\n   154→  - Returns `{ code, url }` if found (url = `https://taunt.bet/r/{code}`)\n   155→  - Returns 404 with `{ error: { code: \"NO_CODE\", message: \"...\" } }` if no code set\n   156→  - Follows same patterns as existing `POST /code` endpoint (auth check, error shape, REFERRAL_BASE_URL)\n   157→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18)\n   158→\n   159→## Iteration 8 — 2026-03-25T11:57:51Z — OK\n   160→- **Log**: iteration-008.log\n   161→\n   162→## Iteration 9 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   163→\n   164→**Item**: [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/apply` — link referee to referrer\n   165→**Status**: Done\n   166→**Changes**:\n   167→- Added `POST /apply` endpoint to `services/backend/src/routes/referral.ts`\n   168→  - Requires JWT auth (wallet from context)\n   169→  - Validates code is non-empty string\n   170→  - Looks up referral code via `db.getReferralCodeByCode(code)` — returns 404 if not found\n   171→  - Self-referral check: rejects if `codeRow.wallet === wallet` (400, SELF_REFERRAL)\n   172→  - Existing referrer check: calls `db.getReferralLinkByReferee(wallet)` — returns 409 if already linked\n   173→  - Creates link via `db.insertReferralLink(referrerWallet, wallet)`\n   174→  - Returns `{ referrer: wallet, benefit: \"10% fee rebate on all games\" }`\n   175→  - Race condition handling: catches unique constraint violation on concurrent insert → 409\n   176→  - Error shape follows spec: `{ error: { code, message, retryable? } }`\n   177→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18)\n   178→\n   179→## Iteration 9 — 2026-03-25T12:01:01Z — OK\n   180→- **Log**: iteration-009.log\n   181→\n   182→## Iteration 10 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   183→\n   184→**Item**: [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/stats` — referral summary stats endpoint\n   185→**Status**: Done\n   186→**Changes**:\n   187→- Added `GET /stats` endpoint to `services/backend/src/routes/referral.ts`\n   188→  - Requires JWT auth (wallet from context)\n   189→  - Calls `db.getReferralStats(wallet)` which returns snake_case `ReferralStats`\n   190→  - Maps to camelCase API response: `referredCount`, `activeCount`, `totalVolumeLamports`, `totalEarnedLamports`, `pendingLamports`\n   191→  - All monetary values are lamport strings (not floats)\n   192→  - Error handling: catches and logs failures, returns 500\n   193→  - Follows existing endpoint patterns (auth check, error shape, logger)\n   194→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18)\n   195→\n   196→## Iteration 10 — 2026-03-25T12:03:21Z — OK\n   197→- **Log**: iteration-010.log\n   198→\n   199→## Iteration 11 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   200→\n   201→**Item**: [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/earnings` — paginated per-game earnings log\n   202→**Status**: Done\n   203→**Changes**:\n   204→- Added `GET /earnings` endpoint to `services/backend/src/routes/referral.ts`\n   205→  - Requires JWT auth (wallet from context)\n   206→  - Query params: `page` (default 1), `limit` (default 20, max 100)\n   207→  - Validates page/limit are positive integers, returns 400 on NaN\n   208→  - Calls `db.getReferralEarnings(wallet, page, limit)` for paginated data\n   209→  - Maps snake_case DB fields to camelCase API response: `roundId`, `gameType`, `refereeWallet`, `wagerLamports`, `earnedLamports`, `createdAt`\n   210→  - All monetary values returned as lamport strings (not numbers)\n   211→  - `createdAt` as ISO-8601 string\n   212→  - Response includes `pagination: { page, totalPages }` per FR-7 contract\n   213→  - Error handling: catches and logs failures, returns 500\n   214→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18)\n   215→\n   216→## Iteration 11 — 2026-03-25T12:05:34Z — OK\n   217→- **Log**: iteration-011.log\n   218→\n   219→## Iteration 12 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   220→\n   221→**Item**: [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/claim` — async claim request with queue event\n   222→**Status**: Done\n   223→**Changes**:\n   224→- Extended `ReferralRoutesDeps` interface to include `sql: postgres.Sql` and `config: Config` (needed for transactional claim and min threshold)\n   225→- Added imports: `postgres`, `Config`, `emitEvent`, `EventTypes`\n   226→- Added `POST /claim` endpoint to `services/backend/src/routes/referral.ts`:\n   227→  - Requires JWT auth (wallet from context)\n   228→  - Snapshots pending balance via `db.getPendingBalance(wallet)`\n   229→  - Rejects zero balance (400, ZERO_BALANCE)\n   230→  - Rejects below threshold (400, BELOW_THRESHOLD) using `config.referralMinClaimLamports`\n   231→  - Uses `sql.begin()` for atomicity: inserts claim row + emits `referral.claim_requested` event in same DB transaction\n   232→  - Event payload: `{ claimId, wallet, amountLamports, requestedAt }`\n   233→  - Returns 202 with `{ claimId, amountLamports, status: \"pending\" }` per FR-7 contract\n   234→  - Error handling: catches and logs failures, returns 500\n   235→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) — no new errors introduced.\n   236→\n   237→## Iteration 12 — 2026-03-25T12:11:41Z — OK\n   238→- **Log**: iteration-012.log\n   239→\n   240→## Iteration 13 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   241→\n   242→**Item**: [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` — poll claim status\n   243→**Status**: Done\n   244→**Changes**:\n   245→- Added `GET /claim/:claimId` endpoint to `services/backend/src/routes/referral.ts`\n   246→  - Requires JWT auth (wallet from context)\n   247→  - Looks up claim by UUID via `db.getReferralClaim(claimId)`\n   248→  - Returns 404 if claim not found OR if claim belongs to a different wallet (prevents enumeration)\n   249→  - Returns `{ claimId, amountLamports, status, txSignature? }` per FR-7 contract\n   250→  - `txSignature` only included when present (completed claims)\n   251→  - `amountLamports` returned as string (lamports-only accounting)\n   252→  - Error handling: catches and logs failures, returns 500\n   253→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) — no new errors introduced.\n   254→\n   255→## Iteration 13 — 2026-03-25T12:14:13Z — OK\n   256→- **Log**: iteration-013.log\n   257→\n   258→## Iteration 14 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   259→\n   260→**Item**: [backend] Register referral routes in `index.ts`, mount at `/referral` prefix with JWT auth middleware\n   261→**Status**: Done\n   262→**Changes**:\n   263→- Added `import { createReferralRoutes } from \"./routes/referral.js\"` to `services/backend/src/index.ts`\n   264→- Added JWT auth middleware for `/referral/*` with `requireAllMethods: true` (ensures auth on GET + POST)\n   265→- Mounted routes with `app.route(\"/referral\", createReferralRoutes({ db, sql, config }))` after profile routes\n   266→- Passes all 3 deps required by `ReferralRoutesDeps`: `db` (from createDb), `sql` (raw postgres connection), `config` (from loadConfig)\n   267→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) — no new errors introduced.\n   268→\n   269→## Iteration 14 — 2026-03-25T12:17:10Z — OK\n   270→- **Log**: iteration-014.log\n   271→\n   272→## Iteration 15 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   273→\n   274→**Item**: [backend] Settlement hook in `settle-tx.ts`: referral earnings recording after game settlement\n   275→**Status**: Done\n   276→**Changes**:\n   277→- Added `referralDefaultRateBps: number` to `SettleTxDeps` interface\n   278→- Added `recordReferralEarnings()` helper function in `settle-tx.ts`:\n   279→  - Takes roundId, gameType, feeBps, referralDefaultRateBps, and player list\n   280→  - Deduplicates players (handles Lord of RNGs multiple entries per player)\n   281→  - For each player: checks `getReferralLinkByReferee()` → if referrer exists, gets rate via `getReferrerRate()` (KOL override)\n   282→  - Calculates `referrerEarned = feeLamports * referrerRateBps / 10000` and `refereeRebate = feeLamports * 1000 / 10000` (fixed 10%)\n   283→  - Inserts via `db.insertReferralEarning()` with all economic inputs preserved\n   284→  - Error handling: duplicate key (idempotent skip), other errors logged but don't fail settlement\n   285→- Called `recordReferralEarnings()` at end of `settleMatch()` (coinflip — 2 players) and `settleLordRound()` (lord — N players)\n   286→- Updated caller in `index.ts` to pass `referralDefaultRateBps: config.referralDefaultRateBps`\n   287→- Updated integration test to pass `referralDefaultRateBps: 1000` in SettleTxDeps\n   288→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) — no new errors introduced.\n   289→\n   290→## Iteration 15 — 2026-03-25T12:25:43Z — OK\n   291→- **Log**: iteration-015.log\n   292→\n   293→## Iteration 16 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   294→\n   295→**Item**: [backend] Wrap settlement DB writes in `sql.transaction()` for atomicity\n   296→**Status**: Done\n   297→**Changes**:\n   298→- Added `withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>` method to `Db` interface in `db.ts`\n   299→- Refactored `createDb()` to accept an optional `_txSql` parameter for transaction injection. When provided, the sql object is used directly (no new connection). `close()` is guarded to only close owned connections.\n   300→- `withTransaction` implementation uses `sql.begin()` to create a transaction scope and passes a transactional `Db` (via recursive `createDb(databaseUrl, txSql)`) to the callback\n   301→- In `settle-tx.ts` `settleMatch()`: wrapped all post-confirmation DB writes (updateRoundPhase, updateRoundEntries, insertOperatorEvent, insertTransaction, recordReferralEarnings) in `db.withTransaction()`\n   302→- In `settle-tx.ts` `settleLordRound()`: same wrapping for Lord of RNGs settlement writes\n   303→- All writes within the transaction use `txDb` instead of `db`, ensuring they share the same transaction connection\n   304→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) — no new errors introduced.\n   305→\n   306→## Iteration 16 — 2026-03-25T12:37:33Z — OK\n   307→- **Log**: iteration-016.log\n   308→\n   309→## Iteration 17 — 2026-03-25 — OK\n   310→\n   311→**Item**: [backend] Register `referral.claim_requested` handler in queue registry\n   312→**Status**: Done\n   313→**Changes**:\n   314→- Created `services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts` with `createClaimHandler()` factory\n   315→  - Accepts `ClaimHandlerDeps`: db, connection, serverKeypair\n   316→  - Returns an `EventHandler` function for the queue worker\n   317→  - Idempotent: skips if claim status is already `completed` or `failed`\n   318→  - Flow: load claim → update to `processing` → re-verify pending balance >= claim amount → build SystemProgram.transfer tx → send + confirm → update to `completed` with tx_signature\n   319→  - On insufficient balance: updates to `failed` with descriptive error (no re-throw, terminal)\n   320→  - On transfer failure: updates to `failed` + re-throws so queue worker retries with exponential backoff\n   321→  - Uses web3.js v1 patterns consistent with settle-tx.ts (Transaction, sign, sendRawTransaction, confirmTransaction)\n   322→- Updated `services/backend/src/index.ts`:\n   323→  - Imported `registerHandler`, `EventTypes` from queue, and `createClaimHandler` from handler\n   324→  - Registered handler before