{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VBMYmD87gNuVHxeAvWmyDw","type":"tool_result","content":"   100→Referred players receive a **fixed 10% rebate on their own fees** (1000 bps of fee_lamports), accruing as a claimable SOL balance. This is permanent and not configurable — every referred player gets 10% back on every game, forever.\n   101→\n   102→**Economics:**\n   103→- On a 1 SOL wager with 500 bps fee: fee = 0.05 SOL, referee rebate = 0.005 SOL\n   104→- Rebate is calculated and stored at settlement time, same transaction as the referrer earning\n   105→- Fee is charged in full on-chain — rebate accrues off-chain as claimable SOL\n   106→- Rebate shares the same claim flow as referrer earnings (unified pending balance per wallet)\n   107→\n   108→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   109→- [ ] After a referred player's game settles, a rebate row is recorded in `referral_earnings.referee_rebate_lamports` <!-- gap: no settlement hook in settle-tx.ts -->\n   110→- [ ] Rebate is exactly 1000 bps of fee_lamports (fixed, not configurable) <!-- gap: no calculation logic implemented -->\n   111→- [ ] Rebate accrues to the referee's claimable balance (same claim flow as referrer earnings) <!-- gap: no claim flow or balance calculation -->\n   112→- [ ] Benefit is communicated in the UI on the referral page and at code entry <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->\n   113→- [ ] A player who is both a referrer AND a referee sees a single combined pending balance <!-- gap: no balance aggregation logic -->\n   114→\n   115→### FR-4: Referrer Fee Share\n   116→\n   117→When a referred player completes a game, the referrer earns a share of the platform fee from that game. This is the core incentive loop.\n   118→\n   119→**Economics:**\n   120→- Default referrer share: **1000 bps of the total fee (= 50 bps of wager)**\n   121→- On a 1 SOL wager: total fee = 0.05 SOL (500 bps), referrer earns 0.005 SOL (1000 bps of the fee)\n   122→- Source: platform fee — no new fees charged to players\n   123→- Duration: **permanent** — referrer earns from their referees' games indefinitely\n   124→- Platform revenue impact: 1000 bps (10%) haircut on fee revenue from referred players (referrer share only; referee reward is non-fee-based)\n   125→\n   126→**KOL override:** Admin can set a custom referrer rate per wallet (stored in DB). This supports partnership agreements where a KOL may receive a higher share (e.g., 2000-3000 bps of total fee). Default rate applies to all non-KOL referrers.\n   127→\n   128→**Settlement hook:** After each game settles, the existing settlement worker checks if the player has a referrer → calculates earnings → inserts into `referral_earnings` table. No additional RPC calls. No on-chain changes.\n   129→\n   130→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   131→- [ ] When a referred player's game settles, the referrer's earning is calculated and stored <!-- gap: no settlement hook -->\n   132→- [ ] Default referrer rate is 1000 bps of the total fee (configurable via environment/config) <!-- gap: no config env var REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS -->\n   133→- [x] KOL wallets can have a custom rate set by admin (stored in `referral_kol_rates` table or equivalent) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates referral_kol_rates with rate_bps, set_by, timestamps -->\n   134→- [x] Earnings are recorded per-game in `referral_earnings` with: referrer, referee, round_id, game_type, wager_lamports, earned_lamports <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql — referral_earnings table has all specified columns -->\n   135→- [x] Referrer earnings accrue indefinitely with no cap or expiry <!-- satisfied: no TTL or cap constraint in 011_referral.sql -->\n   136→\n   137→### FR-5: Earnings Dashboard & Stats\n   138→\n   139→Referrers can view their referral performance and earnings.\n   140→\n   141→**Stats view:**\n   142→- Total referred players\n   143→- Active referred players (played in last 7 days)\n   144→- Total wager volume from referrals\n   145→- Total earnings (all time)\n   146→- Pending (unclaimed) balance\n   147→- Per-game earnings log (paginated)\n   148→\n   149→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   150→- [ ] Referral page shows summary stats (referred count, active count, volume, total earned, pending balance) <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->\n   151→- [ ] Detailed earnings log is available, paginated, showing per-game entries <!-- gap: no GET /referral/earnings endpoint -->\n   152→- [ ] Stats update in near-real-time (within settlement latency, ~3-5s) <!-- gap: no stats endpoint or settlement hook -->\n   153→- [ ] Page is accessible from main navigation or profile section <!-- gap: no sidebar nav item -->\n   154→\n   155→### FR-6: Claim Flow\n   156→\n   157→Referrers can claim their accumulated earnings. Claims are async via the event queue (FR-11) to keep SOL transfers off the request path.\n   158→\n   159→**Flow:** Player clicks \"Claim\" → backend validates balance > minimum threshold → creates claim row with status `pending` + inserts `referral.claim_requested` event in same transaction → returns 202 with claim ID → frontend polls `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` → queue worker acquires claim lock, re-verifies available balance, executes treasury transfer, writes tx signature → claim status updates to `completed` (or `failed`) → frontend shows final state.\n   160→\n   161→**Claim state machine:**\n   162→`pending -> processing -> completed`\n   163→`pending -> processing -> failed` (retryable by queue until max attempts, terminal failure only after retries exhausted)\n   164→\n   165→**Balance snapshot rule:** on claim request, backend snapshots `amount_lamports` from current pending earnings. Handler re-validates this snapshot against unclaimed earnings before transfer to prevent overpay on concurrent requests.\n   166→\n   167→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   168→- [ ] Player can claim their full pending referral balance <!-- gap: no claim endpoint or handler -->\n   169→- [ ] Claim request returns immediately (202 Accepted) with a claim ID for polling <!-- gap: no POST /referral/claim endpoint -->\n   170→- [ ] Queue worker executes the SOL transfer from treasury to player wallet <!-- gap: no claim handler registered -->\n   171→- [x] Claim is recorded with: wallet, amount_lamports, status, timestamps, tx_signature (on success) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql — referral_claims table has all specified columns -->\n   172→- [ ] Concurrent claims from the same wallet are prevented (DB-level locking on balance snapshot) <!-- gap: no claim logic to use locking -->\n   173→- [ ] Zero-balance claims are rejected with a clear error message <!-- gap: no claim endpoint -->\n   174→- [ ] Minimum claim threshold is enforced (e.g., 0.01 SOL) to avoid dust transactions <!-- gap: no threshold config or validation -->\n   175→- [x] Failed transfers are retried by the queue (up to max_attempts) with exponential backoff <!-- satisfied: queue/worker.ts implements exponential backoff (5s→30s→300s) for all event types -->\n   176→\n   177→### FR-7: API Contract\n   178→\n   179→All referral operations are exposed via authenticated REST endpoints.\n   180→\n   181→**Error response shape (all endpoints):**\n   182→`{ error: { code: string, message: string, retryable?: boolean } }`\n   183→\n   184→```\n   185→POST /referral/code                — Set referral code\n   186→  Body: { code: string }\n   187→  Response: { code: string, url: string }\n   188→\n   189→GET  /referral/code                — Get current referral code\n   190→  Response: { code: string, url: string } | 404\n   191→\n   192→POST /referral/apply               — Apply a referral code to current user\n   193→  Body: { code: string }\n   194→  Response: { referrer: string, benefit: string }\n   195→\n   196→GET  /referral/stats               — Get referral summary stats\n   197→  Response: {\n   198→    referredCount: number,\n   199→    activeCount: number,"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aa0285d4-bc35-4024-8afc-77d99fd4e541","uuid":"4ef4bb1f-c138-46b1-a916-a36d5aac335f","timestamp":"2026-03-25T13:43:51.895Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"Referred players receive a **fixed 10% rebate on their own fees** (1000 bps of fee_lamports), accruing as a claimable SOL balance. This is permanent and not configurable — every referred player gets 10% back on every game, forever.\n\n**Economics:**\n- On a 1 SOL wager with 500 bps fee: fee = 0.05 SOL, referee rebate = 0.005 SOL\n- Rebate is calculated and stored at settlement time, same transaction as the referrer earning\n- Fee is charged in full on-chain — rebate accrues off-chain as claimable SOL\n- Rebate shares the same claim flow as referrer earnings (unified pending balance per wallet)\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] After a referred player's game settles, a rebate row is recorded in `referral_earnings.referee_rebate_lamports` <!-- gap: no settlement hook in settle-tx.ts -->\n- [ ] Rebate is exactly 1000 bps of fee_lamports (fixed, not configurable) <!-- gap: no calculation logic implemented -->\n- [ ] Rebate accrues to the referee's claimable balance (same claim flow as referrer earnings) <!-- gap: no claim flow or balance calculation -->\n- [ ] Benefit is communicated in the UI on the referral page and at code entry <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->\n- [ ] A player who is both a referrer AND a referee sees a single combined pending balance <!-- gap: no balance aggregation logic -->\n\n### FR-4: Referrer Fee Share\n\nWhen a referred player completes a game, the referrer earns a share of the platform fee from that game. This is the core incentive loop.\n\n**Economics:**\n- Default referrer share: **1000 bps of the total fee (= 50 bps of wager)**\n- On a 1 SOL wager: total fee = 0.05 SOL (500 bps), referrer earns 0.005 SOL (1000 bps of the fee)\n- Source: platform fee — no new fees charged to players\n- Duration: **permanent** — referrer earns from their referees' games indefinitely\n- Platform revenue impact: 1000 bps (10%) haircut on fee revenue from referred players (referrer share only; referee reward is non-fee-based)\n\n**KOL override:** Admin can set a custom referrer rate per wallet (stored in DB). This supports partnership agreements where a KOL may receive a higher share (e.g., 2000-3000 bps of total fee). Default rate applies to all non-KOL referrers.\n\n**Settlement hook:** After each game settles, the existing settlement worker checks if the player has a referrer → calculates earnings → inserts into `referral_earnings` table. No additional RPC calls. No on-chain changes.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] When a referred player's game settles, the referrer's earning is calculated and stored <!-- gap: no settlement hook -->\n- [ ] Default referrer rate is 1000 bps of the total fee (configurable via environment/config) <!-- gap: no config env var REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS -->\n- [x] KOL wallets can have a custom rate set by admin (stored in `referral_kol_rates` table or equivalent) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates referral_kol_rates with rate_bps, set_by, timestamps -->\n- [x] Earnings are recorded per-game in `referral_earnings` with: referrer, referee, round_id, game_type, wager_lamports, earned_lamports <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql — referral_earnings table has all specified columns -->\n- [x] Referrer earnings accrue indefinitely with no cap or expiry <!-- satisfied: no TTL or cap constraint in 011_referral.sql -->\n\n### FR-5: Earnings Dashboard & Stats\n\nReferrers can view their referral performance and earnings.\n\n**Stats view:**\n- Total referred players\n- Active referred players (played in last 7 days)\n- Total wager volume from referrals\n- Total earnings (all time)\n- Pending (unclaimed) balance\n- Per-game earnings log (paginated)\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Referral page shows summary stats (referred count, active count, volume, total earned, pending balance) <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->\n- [ ] Detailed earnings log is available, paginated, showing per-game entries <!-- gap: no GET /referral/earnings endpoint -->\n- [ ] Stats update in near-real-time (within settlement latency, ~3-5s) <!-- gap: no stats endpoint or settlement hook -->\n- [ ] Page is accessible from main navigation or profile section <!-- gap: no sidebar nav item -->\n\n### FR-6: Claim Flow\n\nReferrers can claim their accumulated earnings. Claims are async via the event queue (FR-11) to keep SOL transfers off the request path.\n\n**Flow:** Player clicks \"Claim\" → backend validates balance > minimum threshold → creates claim row with status `pending` + inserts `referral.claim_requested` event in same transaction → returns 202 with claim ID → frontend polls `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` → queue worker acquires claim lock, re-verifies available balance, executes treasury transfer, writes tx signature → claim status updates to `completed` (or `failed`) → frontend shows final state.\n\n**Claim state machine:**\n`pending -> processing -> completed`\n`pending -> processing -> failed` (retryable by queue until max attempts, terminal failure only after retries exhausted)\n\n**Balance snapshot rule:** on claim request, backend snapshots `amount_lamports` from current pending earnings. Handler re-validates this snapshot against unclaimed earnings before transfer to prevent overpay on concurrent requests.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Player can claim their full pending referral balance <!-- gap: no claim endpoint or handler -->\n- [ ] Claim request returns immediately (202 Accepted) with a claim ID for polling <!-- gap: no POST /referral/claim endpoint -->\n- [ ] Queue worker executes the SOL transfer from treasury to player wallet <!-- gap: no claim handler registered -->\n- [x] Claim is recorded with: wallet, amount_lamports, status, timestamps, tx_signature (on success) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql — referral_claims table has all specified columns -->\n- [ ] Concurrent claims from the same wallet are prevented (DB-level locking on balance snapshot) <!-- gap: no claim logic to use locking -->\n- [ ] Zero-balance claims are rejected with a clear error message <!-- gap: no claim endpoint -->\n- [ ] Minimum claim threshold is enforced (e.g., 0.01 SOL) to avoid dust transactions <!-- gap: no threshold config or validation -->\n- [x] Failed transfers are retried by the queue (up to max_attempts) with exponential backoff <!-- satisfied: queue/worker.ts implements exponential backoff (5s→30s→300s) for all event types -->\n\n### FR-7: API Contract\n\nAll referral operations are exposed via authenticated REST endpoints.\n\n**Error response shape (all endpoints):**\n`{ error: { code: string, message: string, retryable?: boolean } }`\n\n```\nPOST /referral/code                — Set referral code\n  Body: { code: string }\n  Response: { code: string, url: string }\n\nGET  /referral/code                — Get current referral code\n  Response: { code: string, url: string } | 404\n\nPOST /referral/apply               — Apply a referral code to current user\n  Body: { code: string }\n  Response: { referrer: string, benefit: string }\n\nGET  /referral/stats               — Get referral summary stats\n  Response: {\n    referredCount: number,\n    activeCount: number,","numLines":100,"startLine":100,"totalLines":715}}}
