{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015kzCBaDRLALUrPKJfBJ85u","type":"tool_result","content":"   300→\n   301→#### 9a. New Route: `/r/:code` — Referral Link Handler\n   302→\n   303→A lightweight route that captures the referral code from the URL, persists it, and redirects to the home page (or wherever the player was headed).\n   304→\n   305→**Flow:**\n   306→1. Player visits `taunt.bet/r/my-code`\n   307→2. Route component reads `:code` via `useParams()`\n   308→3. Stores `{ code, capturedAt }` in `localStorage` key `referral_code`\n   309→4. Redirects to `/` via `<Navigate to=\"/\" replace />`\n   310→5. On next authentication (in `SessionContext` or a dedicated `useReferralApply` hook), if `referral_code` exists in localStorage and user has no referrer → calls `POST /referral/apply` → clears localStorage on success\n   311→\n   312→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   313→- [ ] Route `/r/:code` registered in `App.tsx` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n   314→- [ ] Code stored in localStorage on visit (no auth required) <!-- gap: no localStorage referral code logic -->\n   315→- [ ] Redirect to `/` happens immediately after capture <!-- gap: no route handler -->\n   316→- [ ] On successful authentication, stored code is applied via API <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n   317→- [ ] localStorage is cleared after successful apply (or if code is invalid/already linked) <!-- gap: no apply logic -->\n   318→- [ ] Invalid/expired codes show a toast notification, not a blocking error <!-- gap: no error handling -->\n   319→\n   320→#### 9b. Sidebar Navigation — Referrals Link\n   321→\n   322→New nav item in the \"Player\" section of `Sidebar.tsx`, between \"Quests\" and the \"Platform\" section.\n   323→\n   324→```tsx\n   325→<NavLink to=\"/referrals\" className={({ isActive }) => `nv-item ${isActive ? \"active\" : \"\"}`}\n   326→  style={{ \"--nc\": \"var(--color-green)\" } as React.CSSProperties}>\n   327→  <div className=\"nv-ico\">\n   328→    {/* share/link icon */}\n   329→  </div>\n   330→  <span className=\"nv-lbl\">Referrals</span>\n   331→</NavLink>\n   332→```\n   333→\n   334→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   335→- [ ] \"Referrals\" nav item appears in sidebar under \"Player\" section <!-- gap: not in Sidebar.tsx -->\n   336→- [ ] Active state styling matches existing nav items <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   337→- [ ] Icon is a share/link-style SVG consistent with sidebar icon style <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   338→- [ ] Navigates to `/referrals` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   339→\n   340→#### 9c. Referral Page (`/referrals`)\n   341→\n   342→Main referral hub page at route `/referrals`. Requires wallet connection + authentication. Shows different states based on whether the player has generated a code yet.\n   343→\n   344→**Layout — top to bottom:**\n   345→\n   346→1. **Your Referral Link** (card)\n   347→   - If no code yet: input field to choose a custom code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button → calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }` → shows link\n   348→   - If code exists: display code + full URL in a styled input/box with a **Copy Link** button\n   349→   - Copy uses `navigator.clipboard.writeText(url)` with a brief \"Copied!\" feedback (tooltip or button text swap)\n   350→   - \"Change code\" link → inline edit field to set a new custom code → calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }`\n   351→\n   352→2. **Stats Summary** (card or stat row)\n   353→   - Four stat boxes in a row: Referred Players | Active (7d) | Total Volume | Total Earned\n   354→   - Values from `GET /referral/stats`\n   355→   - SOL values formatted with `BalanceDisplay` or equivalent (lamports → SOL, 4 decimal places)\n   356→   - Skeleton/loading state while fetching\n   357→\n   358→3. **Pending Earnings + Claim** (card)\n   359→   - Shows pending (unclaimed) balance prominently\n   360→   - \"Claim\" button — enabled only when pending > minimum threshold (0.01 SOL)\n   361→   - Claim flow: button → loading state → calls `POST /referral/claim` → success toast with tx link → refresh stats\n   362→   - Error state: if claim fails, show error message + retry option\n   363→\n   364→4. **Earnings History** (table)\n   365→   - Paginated table from `GET /referral/earnings`\n   366→   - Columns: Date | Game | Referee (truncated wallet) | Wager | Your Earning\n   367→   - Empty state: \"No earnings yet. Share your link to start earning!\"\n   368→   - Pagination controls at bottom (page numbers or \"Load more\")\n   369→\n   370→**Not-connected state:** Show a prompt to connect wallet + brief explanation of the referral program.\n   371→\n   372→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   373→- [ ] Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx`, renders `ReferralPage` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n   374→- [ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description <!-- gap: no ReferralPage component -->\n   375→- [ ] Code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline <!-- gap: no component -->\n   376→- [ ] Setting a code displays the referral URL <!-- gap: no component -->\n   377→- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback <!-- gap: no component -->\n   378→- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton <!-- gap: no component -->\n   379→- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim <!-- gap: no component -->\n   380→- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer) <!-- gap: no component -->\n   381→- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns <!-- gap: no component -->\n   382→- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section <!-- gap: no component -->\n   383→\n   384→#### 9d. Profile Settings — Referral Code Input\n   385→\n   386→In the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n   387→\n   388→**Layout:**\n   389→- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n   390→- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n   391→- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n   392→- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n   393→\n   394→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   395→- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab <!-- gap: not in profile components -->\n   396→- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   397→- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   398→- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   399→- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   400→\n   401→#### 9e. API Client — `lib/referral-api.ts`\n   402→\n   403→Thin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n   404→\n   405→```typescript\n   406→const BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n   407→\n   408→export async function setReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\n   409→export async function getReferralCode(token: string);\n   410→export async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\n   411→export async function getReferralStats(token: string);\n   412→export async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\n   413→export async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\n   414→export async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n   415→```\n   416→\n   417→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   418→- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented (`setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus`) with JWT Bearer auth header <!-- gap: lib/referral-api.ts does not exist -->\n   419→- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   420→- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   421→- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   422→\n   423→#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook — `useReferralApply`\n   424→\n   425→A hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n   426→\n   427→```typescript\n   428→// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\n   429→export function useReferralApply() {\n   430→  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n   431→  const { address } = useWallet();\n   432→\n   433→  useEffect(() => {\n   434→    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n   435→    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n   436→    if (!stored) return;\n   437→    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n   438→    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n   439→      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n   440→      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n   441→  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n   442→}\n   443→```\n   444→\n   445→Mount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n   446→\n   447→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   448→- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n   449→- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   450→- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked) <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   451→- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) — retries next auth <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   452→- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   453→- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   454→\n   455→### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n   456→\n   457→The referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n   458→\n   459→**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n   460→1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n   461→2. If referrer exists → calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports × referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports × fee_bps / 10000)\n   462→3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n   463→4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n   464→\n   465→**Referrer rate lookup:**\n   466→1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n   467→2. If found → use KOL rate\n   468→3. If not → use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n   469→\n   470→**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n   471→\n   472→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   473→- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement <!-- gap: no referral logic in settle-tx.ts -->\n   474→- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager) <!-- gap: no calculation logic -->\n   475→- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise <!-- gap: no rate lookup in settlement -->\n   476→- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity) <!-- gap: no transactional referral write -->\n   477→- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications) <!-- gap: no event emission in settlement -->\n   478→- [ ] No additional RPC calls — purely DB-level <!-- gap: not yet applicable -->\n   479→- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional) <!-- gap: not yet measurable -->\n   480→\n   481→---\n   482→\n   483→### FR-11: Referral Event Contracts + Handler Idempotency\n   484→\n   485→Referral feature handlers are queue consumers built on spec 301 infrastructure.\n   486→\n   487→**Event types (v1):**\n   488→- `referral.claim_requested` — emitted after claim request row is created. Handler sends SOL from treasury.\n   489→\n   490→Note: `referral.game_settled` earnings are written synchronously in the settlement transaction (same DB tx). No async handler needed for earnings — only for claims, where the SOL transfer is the slow/unreliable part.\n   491→\n   492→**Payload contract:**\n   493→\n   494→`referral.claim_requested`\n   495→```json\n   496→{\n   497→  \"claimId\": \"uuid\",\n   498→  \"wallet\": \"string\",\n   499→  \"amountLamports\": \"string\",\n   500→  \"requestedAt\": \"ISO-8601 timestamp\"\n   501→}\n   502→```\n   503→\n   504→**Idempotency key:** `referral:claim:{claimId}`\n   505→\n   506→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   507→- [ ] `referral.claim_requested` event emitted with the payload above when a claim is created <!-- gap: no claim endpoint to emit events -->\n   508→- [ ] Handler validates payload shape; malformed payloads are dead-lettered <!-- gap: no handler registered -->\n   509→- [ ] Handler performs idempotency check: if claim already completed/failed, no-op <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   510→- [ ] Handler re-verifies available balance before transfer (prevents overpay on concurrent claims) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   511→- [ ] Handler sends SOL from treasury to wallet, records tx_signature in `referral_claims` <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   512→- [ ] Re-processing the same event is a safe no-op (no duplicate SOL transfers) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   513→\n   514→---\n   515→\n   516→## Design Decisions (v1)\n   517→\n   518→### Why immutable referrer linkage\n   519→\n   520→- Prevents referral hijacking and user confusion.\n   521→- Simplifies all downstream aggregation and payout logic.\n   522→- Keeps fraud analysis tractable (single parent per user graph).\n   523→\n   524→### Why async claims (not synchronous transfer API)\n   525→\n   526→- Wallet RPC operations are the slowest and least reliable part of the flow.\n   527→- Async queue gives retries/backoff and keeps user request latency low.\n   528→- Prevents backend API threads from being tied up by treasury transfer delays.\n   529→\n   530→### Why persist economic inputs in `referral_earnings`\n   531→\n   532→- Store `fee_lamports` + `referrer_rate_bps` with each earning row to preserve historical correctness.\n   533→- Future rate changes do not retroactively affect past earnings or audits.\n   534→- Makes dispute/debug workflows deterministic from DB data alone.\n   535→\n   536→---\n   537→\n   538→## Success Criteria\n   539→\n   540→- Players can set a custom code, share it, and apply referral codes without friction\n   541→- Referral earnings are calculated correctly and match expected economics (1000 bps of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n   542→- Claim flow delivers SOL to the player's wallet reliably\n   543→- System handles concurrent operations without double-crediting or double-claiming\n   544→- No on-chain program changes required — entirely off-chain for v1\n   545→- Settlement path latency is not measurably affected by referral logic\n   546→- Rewards and claims are processed async via event queue (spec 301) without blocking game loops\n   547→\n   548→---\n   549→\n   550→## Dependencies\n   551→\n   552→- Existing JWT authentication system (spec 007)\n   553→- **Async event queue (spec 301)** — referee rewards and claim payouts are processed via the queue\n   554→- Backend settlement worker (must be extended with referral earnings hook + event emission)\n   555→- Treasury wallet with sufficient SOL for claim payouts\n   556→- Frontend routing for `/r/{CODE}` deep links\n   557→- Environment variables for default referral rate (`REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS=1000`) and claim threshold (`REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS=10000000`)\n   558→\n   559→## Assumptions\n   560→\n   561→- Fee structure is 500 bps (5%) flat fee to single treasury (PlatformConfig on-chain)\n   562→- Treasury wallet is funded and managed outside this spec\n   563→- Referral system launches alongside or after existing games (coinflip, lord-of-rngs)\n   564→- No on-chain enforcement of referral economics needed for v1\n   565→- Postgres `SKIP LOCKED` is available (Postgres 9.5+ — already met)\n   566→\n   567→---\n   568→\n   569→## Validation Plan\n   570→\n   571→| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   572→|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   573→| 1 | Code generation works | API test: generate code, verify format and DB entry | Test output |\n   574→| 2 | Custom codes validated | API test: valid/invalid custom codes | Test output |\n   575→| 3 | Referral linking via URL | E2E: visit /r/CODE, authenticate, verify link created | Test output + DB check |\n   576→| 4 | Manual code entry works | API test: apply code via endpoint | Test output |\n   577→| 5 | Self-referral blocked | API test: apply own code, expect 400 | Test output |\n   578→| 6 | Immutable referrer | API test: apply second code after first, expect 409 | Test output |\n   579→| 7 | Earnings calculated at settlement | Integration test: settle game for referred player, check referral_earnings | Test output + DB check |\n   580→| 8 | KOL custom rate applied | Integration test: set KOL rate, settle game, verify different earning | Test output |\n   581→| 9 | Stats endpoint accurate | API test: create referrals + earnings, verify stats math | Test output |\n   582→| 10 | Claim delivers SOL | Integration test: claim flow, verify tx on-chain | Tx signature |\n   583→| 11 | Concurrent claim prevention | Load test: parallel claims, verify only one succeeds | Test output |\n   584→| 12 | Referee bonus reward granted | Integration test: apply code + complete game, verify reward trigger fired via queue | Test output + DB check |\n   585→| 21 | Async claim completes via queue | Integration test: POST claim → poll status → verify completed with tx sig | Test output + Tx sig |\n   586→| 22 | Welcome reward fires on code apply | Integration test: apply code → verify `referral.code_applied` event processed | Test output + DB check |\n   587→| 23 | Queue infrastructure works (spec 301) | See spec 301 validation plan | Per spec 301 |\n   588→| 13 | `/r/:code` captures + redirects | E2E: visit referral URL, check localStorage, verify redirect to `/` | Browser test |\n   589→| 14 | Auto-apply on auth | E2E: store code in localStorage, connect wallet, verify referral link created + localStorage cleared | Browser test |\n   590→| 15 | Referral page renders all sections | Visual test: code card, stats, claim, earnings table in correct layout | Screenshot |\n   591→| 16 | Copy link works | E2E: click copy button, verify clipboard content matches referral URL | Browser test |\n   592→| 17 | Sidebar nav item present | Visual test: \"Referrals\" link visible in Player section, active state works | Screenshot |\n   593→| 18 | Profile settings code input | E2E: enter code in profile settings, verify referral linked | Browser test |\n   594→| 19 | Unauthenticated state | Visual test: `/referrals` without wallet shows connect prompt | Screenshot |\n   595→| 20 | Claim button states | E2E: disabled when below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with tx link | Browser test |\n   596→\n   597→---\n   598→\n   599→## Completion Signal\n   600→\n   601→### Implementation Checklist\n   602→\n   603→#### Prerequisite\n   604→- [x] [backend] Event queue infrastructure implemented per spec 301 (completed in spec 301)\n   605→\n   606→#### Backend — Database & Core\n   607→- [x] [backend] Database migration `011_referral.sql`: create `referral_codes`, `referral_links`, `referral_earnings`, `referral_claims`, `referral_kol_rates` tables with all constraints and indexes per FR-8 (done: iteration 1)\n   608→- [x] [backend] DB client methods in `db.ts`: `insertReferralCode`, `getReferralCodeByWallet`, `getReferralCodeByCode`, `upsertReferralCode` for code CRUD (done: iteration 3)\n   609→- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralLink`, `getReferralLinkByReferee`, referral link queries (done: iteration 4)\n   610→- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralEarning`, `getPendingBalance(wallet)` (sum referrer_earned where wallet=referrer + sum referee_rebate where wallet=referee, minus completed claims), `getReferralEarnings(wallet, page, limit)`, `getReferralStats(wallet)` (done: iteration 5)\n   611→- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralClaim`, `getReferralClaim`, `updateClaimStatus`, `getReferrerRate(wallet)` (check kol_rates, fallback to env default) (done: iteration 6)\n   612→\n   613→#### Backend — API Endpoints\n   614→- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/code` — set player-chosen code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`, unique). Requires JWT auth. Returns `{ code, url }` (FR-1, FR-7) (done: iteration 7)\n   615→- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/code` — return current code for authenticated wallet, or 404 (FR-7) (done: iteration 8)\n   616→- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/apply` — link referee to referrer. Validate: code exists, no self-referral, no existing referrer. Returns `{ referrer, benefit: \"10% fee rebate on all games\" }` (FR-2, FR-7) (done: iteration 9)\n   617→- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/stats` — return referredCount, activeCount (7d), totalVolumeLamports, totalEarnedLamports, pendingLamports for authenticated wallet. All values as lamport strings (FR-5, FR-7) (done: iteration 10)\n   618→- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/earnings` — paginated per-game earnings log with roundId, gameType, refereeWallet, wagerLamports, earnedLamports, createdAt. Query params: page, limit (FR-5, FR-7) (done: iteration 11)\n   619→- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/claim` — validate pending balance > min threshold (env `REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS`, default 10M = 0.01 SOL), snapshot amount, insert claim row + emit `referral.claim_requested` event in same DB tx. Return 202 `{ claimId, amountLamports, status: \"pending\" }` (FR-6, FR-7) (done: iteration 12)\n   620→- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` — return claim status + txSignature if completed (FR-7) (done: iteration 13)\n   621→- [x] [backend] Register referral routes in `index.ts`, mount at `/referral` prefix with JWT auth middleware (done: iteration 14)\n   622→\n   623→#### Backend — Settlement Integration\n   624→- [x] [backend] Settlement hook in `settle-tx.ts`: after each game settlement DB write, check `referral_links` for the settled player(s). If referrer exists, calculate `referrer_earned = fee_lamports * referrer_rate_bps / 10000` and `referee_rebate = fee_lamports * 1000 / 10000` (fixed 10%). Insert into `referral_earnings` in the same DB transaction. Use `getReferrerRate(wallet)` for KOL override (FR-4, FR-10) (done: iteration 15)\n   625→- [x] [backend] Wrap settlement DB writes in `sql.transaction()` for atomicity — referral earning insert MUST be in the same transaction as the game settlement update (FR-10 + System Invariant 4) (done: iteration 16)\n   626→\n   627→#### Backend — Claim Queue Handler\n   628→- [x] [backend] Register `referral.claim_requested` handler in queue registry: load claim by ID, verify status is `pending`, update to `processing`, re-verify available balance >= claim amount, execute SOL transfer from server keypair (treasury) to wallet, record tx_signature, update status to `completed`. On failure: record error, update status to `failed`. Idempotent: skip if status is already `completed` (FR-6, FR-11) (done: iteration 17)\n   629→\n   630→#### Frontend — API Client & Plumbing\n   631→- [x] [frontend] `lib/referral-api.ts` — 7 typed fetch wrappers with JWT Bearer auth following `auth-api.ts` pattern: `setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus` (FR-9e) (done: iteration 18)\n   632→- [x] [frontend] `/r/:code` route in `App.tsx` — capture code to `localStorage` key `referral_code` as `{ code, capturedAt }`, redirect to `/` via `<Navigate replace />` (FR-9a) (done: iteration 19)\n   633→- [x] [frontend] `useReferralApply` hook — on authentication, if `referral_code` in localStorage and user has no referrer, call `POST /referral/apply`. Clear localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid/already linked). Keep on transient failure. Show success toast. Mount in `App.tsx` inside auth provider tree (FR-9f) (done: iteration 20)\n   634→\n   635→#### Frontend — Referral Page\n   636→- [x] [frontend] Sidebar nav item \"Referrals\" in Player section of `Sidebar.tsx` with share/link icon, `--nc: var(--color-green)`, navigates to `/referrals` (FR-9b) (done: iteration 21)\n   637→- [x] [frontend] `/referrals` route + `ReferralPage` shell: unauthenticated state shows connect-wallet prompt with referral program description. Authenticated state renders feature sections. Wrap in `RouteErrorBoundary` (FR-9c) (done: iteration 22)\n   638→- [x] [frontend] Referral page §1: \"Your Referral Link\" card — custom code input (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button (if none), display code + full URL + Copy Link button with clipboard feedback. \"Change code\" option with inline validation (FR-9c §1) (done: iteration 23)\n   639→- [x] [frontend] Referral page §2: Stats summary card — four stat boxes (Referred Players, Active 7d, Total Volume, Total Earned) from `GET /referral/stats`. SOL values via lamports→SOL formatting. Loading skeleton (FR-9c §2) (done: iteration 24)\n   640→- [x] [frontend] Referral page §3: Pending balance card — show unified pending balance prominently. Breakdown: \"From referrals: X SOL\" + \"From fee rebates: Y SOL\". Claim button disabled below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with Solana explorer tx link (FR-9c §3, FR-6) (done: iteration 25)\n   641→- [x] [frontend] Referral page §4: Earnings history table — paginated from `GET /referral/earnings`. Columns: Date, Game, Referee (truncated wallet), Wager, Your Earning. Empty state message. Pagination controls (FR-9c §4) (done: iteration 26)\n   642→- [x] [frontend] Profile settings: \"Referral Code\" section in profile settings tab. If no referrer: input + Apply button. If already referred: read-only \"Referred by: [wallet]\". Error states inline (FR-9d) (done: iteration 27)\n   643→\n   644→#### Testing\n   645→- [ ] [test] Backend unit tests for referral routes: set custom code (happy path + validation + uniqueness), apply (happy path + self-referral + duplicate), stats, earnings pagination, claim flow (happy + zero balance + below threshold + concurrent)\n   646→- [ ] [test] Backend integration test: settle a game for a referred player → verify `referral_earnings` row with correct referrer_earned + referee_rebate amounts\n   647→- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**` (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs)\n   648→- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in `e2e/visual/**`; run `pnpm test:visual` and update baselines only for intentional UI changes\n   649→- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for `/referrals` page (new page) and sidebar (new nav item). Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures, then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate: **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent) → commit; **REVIEW** (unexpected areas changed) → save diff images to `docs/specs/300-referral-system/visual-review/`, describe concerns; **FAIL** → fix code\n   650→- [ ] [test] If external provider/oracle/VRF integration is included, add devnet real-provider E2E coverage in `e2e/devnet/**` with env validation + retry/backoff (or mark N/A with reason)\n   651→\n   652→### Testing Requirements\n   653→\n   654→The agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n   655→\n   656→#### Code Quality\n   657→- [ ] All existing tests pass\n   658→- [ ] New tests added for new functionality\n   659→- [ ] No lint errors\n   660→\n   661→#### Functional Verification\n   662→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n   663→- [ ] Edge cases handled\n   664→- [ ] Error states handled\n   665→\n   666→#### Visual Regression\n   667→- [ ] `pnpm test:visual` passes (all baselines match)\n   668→- [ ] If this spec changes UI: affected baselines regenerated and committed\n   669→- [ ] Local deterministic E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e`) for user-facing flows, or N/A documented\n   670→- [ ] Devnet real-provider E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`) when provider-backed flows are included\n   671→\n   672→#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n   673→- [ ] Desktop view correct\n   674→- [ ] Mobile view correct\n   675→\n   676→#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n   677→- [ ] No JS console errors\n   678→- [ ] No failed network requests\n   679→\n   680→#### Smoke Test (Human-in-the-Loop)\n   681→\n   682→Before declaring done, trace every user-facing flow and verify the experience\n   683→makes sense from a player's perspective.\n   684→\n   685→- [ ] Set custom referral code → copy link → verify URL format\n   686→- [ ] Visit referral link in incognito → authenticate → verify referrer linked\n   687→- [ ] Manually enter code in settings → verify referrer linked\n   688→- [ ] Play a game as referred player → verify referrer earnings appear\n   689→- [ ] Referrer dashboard shows correct stats\n   690→- [ ] Claim earnings → verify SOL arrives in wallet\n   691→- [ ] Attempt self-referral → verify blocked\n   692→- [ ] Attempt to change referrer → verify blocked\n   693→- [ ] Referee fee rebate accrues after playing a game (visible in pending balance)\n   694→- [ ] Referral page shows breakdown: \"From referrals: X\" + \"From fee rebates: Y\"\n   695→\n   696→### Iteration Instructions\n   697→\n   698→If ANY check fails:\n   699→1. Identify the specific issue\n   700→2. Fix the code\n   701→3. Re-run tests\n   702→4. Re-verify all criteria\n   703→5. Check again\n   704→\n   705→**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n   706→\n   707→### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n   708→\n   709→After the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n   710→`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n   711→1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n   712→2. Writes `docs/specs/{id}/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n   713→3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n   714→4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n   715→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aa0285d4-bc35-4024-8afc-77d99fd4e541","uuid":"fb6c65c0-5375-41cc-8e67-8f196a909efc","timestamp":"2026-03-25T13:43:59.795Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"\n#### 9a. New Route: `/r/:code` — Referral Link Handler\n\nA lightweight route that captures the referral code from the URL, persists it, and redirects to the home page (or wherever the player was headed).\n\n**Flow:**\n1. Player visits `taunt.bet/r/my-code`\n2. Route component reads `:code` via `useParams()`\n3. Stores `{ code, capturedAt }` in `localStorage` key `referral_code`\n4. Redirects to `/` via `<Navigate to=\"/\" replace />`\n5. On next authentication (in `SessionContext` or a dedicated `useReferralApply` hook), if `referral_code` exists in localStorage and user has no referrer → calls `POST /referral/apply` → clears localStorage on success\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Route `/r/:code` registered in `App.tsx` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n- [ ] Code stored in localStorage on visit (no auth required) <!-- gap: no localStorage referral code logic -->\n- [ ] Redirect to `/` happens immediately after capture <!-- gap: no route handler -->\n- [ ] On successful authentication, stored code is applied via API <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n- [ ] localStorage is cleared after successful apply (or if code is invalid/already linked) <!-- gap: no apply logic -->\n- [ ] Invalid/expired codes show a toast notification, not a blocking error <!-- gap: no error handling -->\n\n#### 9b. Sidebar Navigation — Referrals Link\n\nNew nav item in the \"Player\" section of `Sidebar.tsx`, between \"Quests\" and the \"Platform\" section.\n\n```tsx\n<NavLink to=\"/referrals\" className={({ isActive }) => `nv-item ${isActive ? \"active\" : \"\"}`}\n  style={{ \"--nc\": \"var(--color-green)\" } as React.CSSProperties}>\n  <div className=\"nv-ico\">\n    {/* share/link icon */}\n  </div>\n  <span className=\"nv-lbl\">Referrals</span>\n</NavLink>\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] \"Referrals\" nav item appears in sidebar under \"Player\" section <!-- gap: not in Sidebar.tsx -->\n- [ ] Active state styling matches existing nav items <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Icon is a share/link-style SVG consistent with sidebar icon style <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Navigates to `/referrals` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9c. Referral Page (`/referrals`)\n\nMain referral hub page at route `/referrals`. Requires wallet connection + authentication. Shows different states based on whether the player has generated a code yet.\n\n**Layout — top to bottom:**\n\n1. **Your Referral Link** (card)\n   - If no code yet: input field to choose a custom code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button → calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }` → shows link\n   - If code exists: display code + full URL in a styled input/box with a **Copy Link** button\n   - Copy uses `navigator.clipboard.writeText(url)` with a brief \"Copied!\" feedback (tooltip or button text swap)\n   - \"Change code\" link → inline edit field to set a new custom code → calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }`\n\n2. **Stats Summary** (card or stat row)\n   - Four stat boxes in a row: Referred Players | Active (7d) | Total Volume | Total Earned\n   - Values from `GET /referral/stats`\n   - SOL values formatted with `BalanceDisplay` or equivalent (lamports → SOL, 4 decimal places)\n   - Skeleton/loading state while fetching\n\n3. **Pending Earnings + Claim** (card)\n   - Shows pending (unclaimed) balance prominently\n   - \"Claim\" button — enabled only when pending > minimum threshold (0.01 SOL)\n   - Claim flow: button → loading state → calls `POST /referral/claim` → success toast with tx link → refresh stats\n   - Error state: if claim fails, show error message + retry option\n\n4. **Earnings History** (table)\n   - Paginated table from `GET /referral/earnings`\n   - Columns: Date | Game | Referee (truncated wallet) | Wager | Your Earning\n   - Empty state: \"No earnings yet. Share your link to start earning!\"\n   - Pagination controls at bottom (page numbers or \"Load more\")\n\n**Not-connected state:** Show a prompt to connect wallet + brief explanation of the referral program.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx`, renders `ReferralPage` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n- [ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description <!-- gap: no ReferralPage component -->\n- [ ] Code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Setting a code displays the referral URL <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer) <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section <!-- gap: no component -->\n\n#### 9d. Profile Settings — Referral Code Input\n\nIn the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n\n**Layout:**\n- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab <!-- gap: not in profile components -->\n- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9e. API Client — `lib/referral-api.ts`\n\nThin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n\n```typescript\nconst BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n\nexport async function setReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\nexport async function getReferralCode(token: string);\nexport async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\nexport async function getReferralStats(token: string);\nexport async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\nexport async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\nexport async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented (`setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus`) with JWT Bearer auth header <!-- gap: lib/referral-api.ts does not exist -->\n- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook — `useReferralApply`\n\nA hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n\n```typescript\n// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\nexport function useReferralApply() {\n  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n  const { address } = useWallet();\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n    if (!stored) return;\n    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n}\n```\n\nMount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked) <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) — retries next auth <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page <!-- gap: no hook -->\n\n### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n\nThe referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n\n**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n2. If referrer exists → calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports × referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports × fee_bps / 10000)\n3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n\n**Referrer rate lookup:**\n1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n2. If found → use KOL rate\n3. If not → use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n\n**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement <!-- gap: no referral logic in settle-tx.ts -->\n- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager) <!-- gap: no calculation logic -->\n- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise <!-- gap: no rate lookup in settlement -->\n- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity) <!-- gap: no transactional referral write -->\n- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications) <!-- gap: no event emission in settlement -->\n- [ ] No additional RPC calls — purely DB-level <!-- gap: not yet applicable -->\n- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional) <!-- gap: not yet measurable -->\n\n---\n\n### FR-11: Referral Event Contracts + Handler Idempotency\n\nReferral feature handlers are queue consumers built on spec 301 infrastructure.\n\n**Event types (v1):**\n- `referral.claim_requested` — emitted after claim request row is created. Handler sends SOL from treasury.\n\nNote: `referral.game_settled` earnings are written synchronously in the settlement transaction (same DB tx). No async handler needed for earnings — only for claims, where the SOL transfer is the slow/unreliable part.\n\n**Payload contract:**\n\n`referral.claim_requested`\n```json\n{\n  \"claimId\": \"uuid\",\n  \"wallet\": \"string\",\n  \"amountLamports\": \"string\",\n  \"requestedAt\": \"ISO-8601 timestamp\"\n}\n```\n\n**Idempotency key:** `referral:claim:{claimId}`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] `referral.claim_requested` event emitted with the payload above when a claim is created <!-- gap: no claim endpoint to emit events -->\n- [ ] Handler validates payload shape; malformed payloads are dead-lettered <!-- gap: no handler registered -->\n- [ ] Handler performs idempotency check: if claim already completed/failed, no-op <!-- gap: no handler -->\n- [ ] Handler re-verifies available balance before transfer (prevents overpay on concurrent claims) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n- [ ] Handler sends SOL from treasury to wallet, records tx_signature in `referral_claims` <!-- gap: no handler -->\n- [ ] Re-processing the same event is a safe no-op (no duplicate SOL transfers) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n\n---\n\n## Design Decisions (v1)\n\n### Why immutable referrer linkage\n\n- Prevents referral hijacking and user confusion.\n- Simplifies all downstream aggregation and payout logic.\n- Keeps fraud analysis tractable (single parent per user graph).\n\n### Why async claims (not synchronous transfer API)\n\n- Wallet RPC operations are the slowest and least reliable part of the flow.\n- Async queue gives retries/backoff and keeps user request latency low.\n- Prevents backend API threads from being tied up by treasury transfer delays.\n\n### Why persist economic inputs in `referral_earnings`\n\n- Store `fee_lamports` + `referrer_rate_bps` with each earning row to preserve historical correctness.\n- Future rate changes do not retroactively affect past earnings or audits.\n- Makes dispute/debug workflows deterministic from DB data alone.\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Players can set a custom code, share it, and apply referral codes without friction\n- Referral earnings are calculated correctly and match expected economics (1000 bps of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n- Claim flow delivers SOL to the player's wallet reliably\n- System handles concurrent operations without double-crediting or double-claiming\n- No on-chain program changes required — entirely off-chain for v1\n- Settlement path latency is not measurably affected by referral logic\n- Rewards and claims are processed async via event queue (spec 301) without blocking game loops\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Existing JWT authentication system (spec 007)\n- **Async event queue (spec 301)** — referee rewards and claim payouts are processed via the queue\n- Backend settlement worker (must be extended with referral earnings hook + event emission)\n- Treasury wallet with sufficient SOL for claim payouts\n- Frontend routing for `/r/{CODE}` deep links\n- Environment variables for default referral rate (`REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS=1000`) and claim threshold (`REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS=10000000`)\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- Fee structure is 500 bps (5%) flat fee to single treasury (PlatformConfig on-chain)\n- Treasury wallet is funded and managed outside this spec\n- Referral system launches alongside or after existing games (coinflip, lord-of-rngs)\n- No on-chain enforcement of referral economics needed for v1\n- Postgres `SKIP LOCKED` is available (Postgres 9.5+ — already met)\n\n---\n\n## Validation Plan\n\n| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | Code generation works | API test: generate code, verify format and DB entry | Test output |\n| 2 | Custom codes validated | API test: valid/invalid custom codes | Test output |\n| 3 | Referral linking via URL | E2E: visit /r/CODE, authenticate, verify link created | Test output + DB check |\n| 4 | Manual code entry works | API test: apply code via endpoint | Test output |\n| 5 | Self-referral blocked | API test: apply own code, expect 400 | Test output |\n| 6 | Immutable referrer | API test: apply second code after first, expect 409 | Test output |\n| 7 | Earnings calculated at settlement | Integration test: settle game for referred player, check referral_earnings | Test output + DB check |\n| 8 | KOL custom rate applied | Integration test: set KOL rate, settle game, verify different earning | Test output |\n| 9 | Stats endpoint accurate | API test: create referrals + earnings, verify stats math | Test output |\n| 10 | Claim delivers SOL | Integration test: claim flow, verify tx on-chain | Tx signature |\n| 11 | Concurrent claim prevention | Load test: parallel claims, verify only one succeeds | Test output |\n| 12 | Referee bonus reward granted | Integration test: apply code + complete game, verify reward trigger fired via queue | Test output + DB check |\n| 21 | Async claim completes via queue | Integration test: POST claim → poll status → verify completed with tx sig | Test output + Tx sig |\n| 22 | Welcome reward fires on code apply | Integration test: apply code → verify `referral.code_applied` event processed | Test output + DB check |\n| 23 | Queue infrastructure works (spec 301) | See spec 301 validation plan | Per spec 301 |\n| 13 | `/r/:code` captures + redirects | E2E: visit referral URL, check localStorage, verify redirect to `/` | Browser test |\n| 14 | Auto-apply on auth | E2E: store code in localStorage, connect wallet, verify referral link created + localStorage cleared | Browser test |\n| 15 | Referral page renders all sections | Visual test: code card, stats, claim, earnings table in correct layout | Screenshot |\n| 16 | Copy link works | E2E: click copy button, verify clipboard content matches referral URL | Browser test |\n| 17 | Sidebar nav item present | Visual test: \"Referrals\" link visible in Player section, active state works | Screenshot |\n| 18 | Profile settings code input | E2E: enter code in profile settings, verify referral linked | Browser test |\n| 19 | Unauthenticated state | Visual test: `/referrals` without wallet shows connect prompt | Screenshot |\n| 20 | Claim button states | E2E: disabled when below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with tx link | Browser test |\n\n---\n\n## Completion Signal\n\n### Implementation Checklist\n\n#### Prerequisite\n- [x] [backend] Event queue infrastructure implemented per spec 301 (completed in spec 301)\n\n#### Backend — Database & Core\n- [x] [backend] Database migration `011_referral.sql`: create `referral_codes`, `referral_links`, `referral_earnings`, `referral_claims`, `referral_kol_rates` tables with all constraints and indexes per FR-8 (done: iteration 1)\n- [x] [backend] DB client methods in `db.ts`: `insertReferralCode`, `getReferralCodeByWallet`, `getReferralCodeByCode`, `upsertReferralCode` for code CRUD (done: iteration 3)\n- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralLink`, `getReferralLinkByReferee`, referral link queries (done: iteration 4)\n- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralEarning`, `getPendingBalance(wallet)` (sum referrer_earned where wallet=referrer + sum referee_rebate where wallet=referee, minus completed claims), `getReferralEarnings(wallet, page, limit)`, `getReferralStats(wallet)` (done: iteration 5)\n- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralClaim`, `getReferralClaim`, `updateClaimStatus`, `getReferrerRate(wallet)` (check kol_rates, fallback to env default) (done: iteration 6)\n\n#### Backend — API Endpoints\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/code` — set player-chosen code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`, unique). Requires JWT auth. Returns `{ code, url }` (FR-1, FR-7) (done: iteration 7)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/code` — return current code for authenticated wallet, or 404 (FR-7) (done: iteration 8)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/apply` — link referee to referrer. Validate: code exists, no self-referral, no existing referrer. Returns `{ referrer, benefit: \"10% fee rebate on all games\" }` (FR-2, FR-7) (done: iteration 9)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/stats` — return referredCount, activeCount (7d), totalVolumeLamports, totalEarnedLamports, pendingLamports for authenticated wallet. All values as lamport strings (FR-5, FR-7) (done: iteration 10)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/earnings` — paginated per-game earnings log with roundId, gameType, refereeWallet, wagerLamports, earnedLamports, createdAt. Query params: page, limit (FR-5, FR-7) (done: iteration 11)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/claim` — validate pending balance > min threshold (env `REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS`, default 10M = 0.01 SOL), snapshot amount, insert claim row + emit `referral.claim_requested` event in same DB tx. Return 202 `{ claimId, amountLamports, status: \"pending\" }` (FR-6, FR-7) (done: iteration 12)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` — return claim status + txSignature if completed (FR-7) (done: iteration 13)\n- [x] [backend] Register referral routes in `index.ts`, mount at `/referral` prefix with JWT auth middleware (done: iteration 14)\n\n#### Backend — Settlement Integration\n- [x] [backend] Settlement hook in `settle-tx.ts`: after each game settlement DB write, check `referral_links` for the settled player(s). If referrer exists, calculate `referrer_earned = fee_lamports * referrer_rate_bps / 10000` and `referee_rebate = fee_lamports * 1000 / 10000` (fixed 10%). Insert into `referral_earnings` in the same DB transaction. Use `getReferrerRate(wallet)` for KOL override (FR-4, FR-10) (done: iteration 15)\n- [x] [backend] Wrap settlement DB writes in `sql.transaction()` for atomicity — referral earning insert MUST be in the same transaction as the game settlement update (FR-10 + System Invariant 4) (done: iteration 16)\n\n#### Backend — Claim Queue Handler\n- [x] [backend] Register `referral.claim_requested` handler in queue registry: load claim by ID, verify status is `pending`, update to `processing`, re-verify available balance >= claim amount, execute SOL transfer from server keypair (treasury) to wallet, record tx_signature, update status to `completed`. On failure: record error, update status to `failed`. Idempotent: skip if status is already `completed` (FR-6, FR-11) (done: iteration 17)\n\n#### Frontend — API Client & Plumbing\n- [x] [frontend] `lib/referral-api.ts` — 7 typed fetch wrappers with JWT Bearer auth following `auth-api.ts` pattern: `setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus` (FR-9e) (done: iteration 18)\n- [x] [frontend] `/r/:code` route in `App.tsx` — capture code to `localStorage` key `referral_code` as `{ code, capturedAt }`, redirect to `/` via `<Navigate replace />` (FR-9a) (done: iteration 19)\n- [x] [frontend] `useReferralApply` hook — on authentication, if `referral_code` in localStorage and user has no referrer, call `POST /referral/apply`. Clear localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid/already linked). Keep on transient failure. Show success toast. Mount in `App.tsx` inside auth provider tree (FR-9f) (done: iteration 20)\n\n#### Frontend — Referral Page\n- [x] [frontend] Sidebar nav item \"Referrals\" in Player section of `Sidebar.tsx` with share/link icon, `--nc: var(--color-green)`, navigates to `/referrals` (FR-9b) (done: iteration 21)\n- [x] [frontend] `/referrals` route + `ReferralPage` shell: unauthenticated state shows connect-wallet prompt with referral program description. Authenticated state renders feature sections. Wrap in `RouteErrorBoundary` (FR-9c) (done: iteration 22)\n- [x] [frontend] Referral page §1: \"Your Referral Link\" card — custom code input (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button (if none), display code + full URL + Copy Link button with clipboard feedback. \"Change code\" option with inline validation (FR-9c §1) (done: iteration 23)\n- [x] [frontend] Referral page §2: Stats summary card — four stat boxes (Referred Players, Active 7d, Total Volume, Total Earned) from `GET /referral/stats`. SOL values via lamports→SOL formatting. Loading skeleton (FR-9c §2) (done: iteration 24)\n- [x] [frontend] Referral page §3: Pending balance card — show unified pending balance prominently. Breakdown: \"From referrals: X SOL\" + \"From fee rebates: Y SOL\". Claim button disabled below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with Solana explorer tx link (FR-9c §3, FR-6) (done: iteration 25)\n- [x] [frontend] Referral page §4: Earnings history table — paginated from `GET /referral/earnings`. Columns: Date, Game, Referee (truncated wallet), Wager, Your Earning. Empty state message. Pagination controls (FR-9c §4) (done: iteration 26)\n- [x] [frontend] Profile settings: \"Referral Code\" section in profile settings tab. If no referrer: input + Apply button. If already referred: read-only \"Referred by: [wallet]\". Error states inline (FR-9d) (done: iteration 27)\n\n#### Testing\n- [ ] [test] Backend unit tests for referral routes: set custom code (happy path + validation + uniqueness), apply (happy path + self-referral + duplicate), stats, earnings pagination, claim flow (happy + zero balance + below threshold + concurrent)\n- [ ] [test] Backend integration test: settle a game for a referred player → verify `referral_earnings` row with correct referrer_earned + referee_rebate amounts\n- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**` (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs)\n- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in `e2e/visual/**`; run `pnpm test:visual` and update baselines only for intentional UI changes\n- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for `/referrals` page (new page) and sidebar (new nav item). Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures, then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate: **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent) → commit; **REVIEW** (unexpected areas changed) → save diff images to `docs/specs/300-referral-system/visual-review/`, describe concerns; **FAIL** → fix code\n- [ ] [test] If external provider/oracle/VRF integration is included, add devnet real-provider E2E coverage in `e2e/devnet/**` with env validation + retry/backoff (or mark N/A with reason)\n\n### Testing Requirements\n\nThe agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n\n#### Code Quality\n- [ ] All existing tests pass\n- [ ] New tests added for new functionality\n- [ ] No lint errors\n\n#### Functional Verification\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n- [ ] Edge cases handled\n- [ ] Error states handled\n\n#### Visual Regression\n- [ ] `pnpm test:visual` passes (all baselines match)\n- [ ] If this spec changes UI: affected baselines regenerated and committed\n- [ ] Local deterministic E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e`) for user-facing flows, or N/A documented\n- [ ] Devnet real-provider E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`) when provider-backed flows are included\n\n#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n- [ ] Desktop view correct\n- [ ] Mobile view correct\n\n#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n- [ ] No JS console errors\n- [ ] No failed network requests\n\n#### Smoke Test (Human-in-the-Loop)\n\nBefore declaring done, trace every user-facing flow and verify the experience\nmakes sense from a player's perspective.\n\n- [ ] Set custom referral code → copy link → verify URL format\n- [ ] Visit referral link in incognito → authenticate → verify referrer linked\n- [ ] Manually enter code in settings → verify referrer linked\n- [ ] Play a game as referred player → verify referrer earnings appear\n- [ ] Referrer dashboard shows correct stats\n- [ ] Claim earnings → verify SOL arrives in wallet\n- [ ] Attempt self-referral → verify blocked\n- [ ] Attempt to change referrer → verify blocked\n- [ ] Referee fee rebate accrues after playing a game (visible in pending balance)\n- [ ] Referral page shows breakdown: \"From referrals: X\" + \"From fee rebates: Y\"\n\n### Iteration Instructions\n\nIf ANY check fails:\n1. Identify the specific issue\n2. Fix the code\n3. Re-run tests\n4. Re-verify all criteria\n5. Check again\n\n**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n\n### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n\nAfter the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n2. Writes `docs/specs/{id}/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n","numLines":416,"startLine":300,"totalLines":715}}}
