{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FUmw22Gty3DEJ8iw5RHp6J","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive view of the backend test structure. Let me create a detailed analysis report.\n\n## Backend Test Files Analysis Report\n\nI've completed a thorough analysis of the backend test infrastructure in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/`. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Test Files Overview**\n\nThe backend has **8 test files** organized by functionality:\n\n| File | Purpose | Lines |\n|------|---------|-------|\n| `src/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` | Full HTTP endpoint stack (middleware + routes) | 451 |\n| `src/__tests__/auth-routes.test.ts` | Auth flow (challenge → verify → refresh → logout) | 298 |\n| `src/__tests__/auth.test.ts` | JWT middleware unit tests | 103 |\n| `src/__tests__/rate-limit.test.ts` | Rate limiter middleware unit tests | 88 |\n| `src/__tests__/fairness.test.ts` | Fairness utility functions (secrets, commitments, PDAs) | 121 |\n| `src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` | Full lifecycle (create → join → settle) | 200+ |\n| `src/queue/__tests__/queue.test.ts` | Event queue unit tests | 157 |\n| `src/queue/__tests__/queue-integration.test.ts` | Event queue worker integration | 150+ |\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Test Framework & Configuration**\n\n**Test Runner:** **Vitest**\n- Configuration file: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/vitest.config.ts`\n- Key setting: `fileParallelism: false` — tests run sequentially to avoid database TRUNCATE races\n\n**Package Manager:** pnpm  \n**Test Command:** `pnpm test` (runs `vitest --passWithNoTests`)\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `vitest@^2.1.0`\n- `postgres@^3.4.0` (database client)\n- `jose@^6.0.0` (JWT signing/verification)\n- `@solana/web3.js@^1.98.0` (keypair/pubkey utilities)\n- `tweetnacl@^1.0.3` (Ed25519 signatures)\n- `bs58@^6.0.0` (base58 encoding/decoding)\n\n**Environment:** Node.js (target: node)\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Testing Architecture Patterns**\n\n#### **A. Middleware Unit Tests** (`auth.test.ts`, `rate-limit.test.ts`)\n\nPattern: **Middleware → Test App → Request → Assert**\n\n```typescript\n// 1. Create a minimal Hono app with the middleware\nfunction createTestApp() {\n  const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();\n  app.use(\"/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: JWT_SECRET }));\n  app.post(\"/test\", (c) => c.json({ ok: true, wallet: c.get(\"wallet\") }));\n  return app;\n}\n\n// 2. Make a request using Hono's built-in request handler\nconst res = await app.request(\"/test\", {\n  method: \"POST\",\n  headers: { \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${token}` },\n  body: JSON.stringify(data),\n});\n\n// 3. Assert response status and JSON\nexpect(res.status).toBe(200);\nconst json = (await res.json()) as Record<string, unknown>;\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Uses **Hono's native `.request()` method** (no external HTTP library)\n- JWT tokens created with `jose.SignJWT`\n- Middleware tested in isolation with minimal dependencies\n- Tests cover both happy paths and edge cases (expired token, wrong secret, missing header)\n\n---\n\n#### **B. Endpoint Tests** (`endpoints.test.ts`)\n\nPattern: **Full middleware stack + routes + database**\n\n```typescript\n// 1. Setup: database + mock connection\nlet db: Db;\nlet mockConn: MockConnection;  // Minimal mock of web3.js Connection\n\nbeforeAll(async () => {\n  db = createDb(DATABASE_URL);  // Real Postgres\n  rawSql = postgres(DATABASE_URL);\n});\n\nbeforeEach(async () => {\n  await rawSql`TRUNCATE rounds, operator_events RESTART IDENTITY`;  // Clean state\n});\n\n// 2. Build app with FULL middleware stack\nfunction buildApp(opts?: { perWallet?: number; global?: number }) {\n  const app = new Hono();\n  \n  // Chain middleware and routes\n  app.use(\"/fairness/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: JWT_SECRET }));\n  app.use(\"/fairness/*\", createRateLimitMiddleware({ ... }));\n  app.route(\"/fairness/coinflip\", createCoinflipRoutes({ db, connection: mockConn, ... }));\n  app.route(\"/fairness/rounds\", createRoundsRoutes({ db }));\n  app.route(\"/health\", createHealthRoutes({ ... }));\n  \n  return app;\n}\n\n// 3. Test scenarios\nit(\"returns 200 with valid JWT\", async () => {\n  const token = await makeJwt(wallet);\n  const res = await app.request(\"/fairness/coinflip/create\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${token}` },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ wallet, amountLamports: 5_000_000, side: 0 }),\n  });\n  expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n  const json = (await res.json()) as Record<string, unknown>;\n  expect(json.transaction).toBeDefined();\n  expect(json.matchPda).toBeDefined();\n});\n```\n\n**Test Coverage Scope:**\n- ✅ **Auth**: missing JWT (401), expired JWT (401), wallet mismatch (403)\n- ✅ **Rate Limit**: per-wallet limit (429), global limit (429), `Retry-After` header\n- ✅ **Routes**: \n  - `POST /fairness/coinflip/create` — with various JWT states + collision detection\n  - `POST /fairness/lord/create` — valid JWT, response shape\n  - `GET /fairness/rounds/:pda` — known PDA (200), unknown PDA (404)\n  - `GET /health` — status fields, unsettled round count\n- ✅ **Mocking**: Database operations, RPC calls\n\n---\n\n#### **C. Auth Routes Integration Tests** (`auth-routes.test.ts`)\n\nPattern: **Full flow testing with real database**\n\n```typescript\n// Challenge → Sign → Verify → Refresh → Logout → Test Reuse Detection\n\nit(\"full auth flow: challenge → verify → refresh → logout\", async () => {\n  // 1. POST /auth/challenge → get nonce + message\n  const challengeRes = await app.request(\"/auth/challenge\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    body: JSON.stringify({ wallet }),\n  });\n  const { nonce, message } = await challengeRes.json();\n\n  // 2. Sign message with Keypair (nacl.sign.detached)\n  const messageBytes = new TextEncoder().encode(message);\n  const signatureBytes = nacl.sign.detached(messageBytes, creatorKeypair.secretKey);\n  const signature = bs58.encode(signatureBytes);\n\n  // 3. POST /auth/verify → get accessToken + refreshToken\n  const verifyRes = await app.request(\"/auth/verify\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    body: JSON.stringify({ nonce, wallet, signature }),\n  });\n  const tokens = await verifyRes.json();\n  expect(tokens.accessToken).toBeDefined();\n  expect(tokens.refreshToken).toBeDefined();\n\n  // 4. POST /auth/refresh → get new tokens (old token rotated)\n  const refreshRes = await app.request(\"/auth/refresh\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken: tokens.refreshToken }),\n  });\n  const newTokens = await refreshRes.json();\n  expect(newTokens.refreshToken).not.toBe(tokens.refreshToken);  // Rotated\n\n  // 5. Replay old token → fails (401) with \"reuse\" error\n  const replayRes = await app.request(\"/auth/refresh\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken: tokens.refreshToken }),\n  });\n  expect(replayRes.status).toBe(401);\n  expect((await replayRes.json()).error).toContain(\"reuse\");\n\n  // 6. POST /auth/logout → 204\n  const logoutRes = await app.request(\"/auth/logout\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken: newTokens.refreshToken }),\n  });\n  expect(logoutRes.status).toBe(204);\n\n  // 7. POST-logout refresh fails\n  const postLogoutRes = await app.request(\"/auth/refresh\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken: newTokens.refreshToken }),\n  });\n  expect(postLogoutRes.status).toBe(401);\n});\n```\n\n**Edge Cases Tested:**\n- ✅ Wrong wallet claim with correct signature (401)\n- ✅ Correct wallet with wrong signature (401)\n- ✅ Nonce reuse prevention\n- ✅ Refresh token rotation\n- ✅ Logout revocation\n\n---\n\n#### **D. Fairness Unit Tests** (`fairness.test.ts`)\n\nPattern: **Pure function unit tests with deterministic checks**\n\n```typescript\ndescribe(\"computeCommitment\", () => {\n  it(\"matches packages/fairness commitment algorithm\", () => {\n    const seedHex = \"abcdef0123456789...\";\n    const seedBytes = Buffer.from(seedHex, \"hex\");\n    \n    const backendCommitment = computeCommitment(seedBytes).toString(\"hex\");\n    \n    // Cross-check with Node crypto for verification\n    const nodeCommitment = createHash(\"sha256\").update(seedBytes).digest(\"hex\");\n    \n    expect(backendCommitment).toBe(nodeCommitment);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe(\"deriveMatchPda\", () => {\n  it(\"matches manual PDA derivation with seeds [match, creator, matchId]\", () => {\n    const matchId = Buffer.from(\"deadbeef01234567\", \"hex\");\n    \n    const [expected] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n      [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer(), matchId],\n      programId,\n    );\n    \n    const [actual] = deriveMatchPda(creator, matchId);\n    expect(actual.equals(expected)).toBe(true);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Functions Tested:**\n- ✅ `generateSecret()` — 32 bytes, unique per call\n- ✅ `computeCommitment()` — SHA256 determinism, cross-package agreement\n- ✅ `generateMatchId()` — 8 bytes, unique per call\n- ✅ `deriveMatchPda()` — PDA derivation correctness, determinism, different creators/matchIds\n\n---\n\n#### **E. Integration Tests** (`integration.test.ts`)\n\nPattern: **Full lifecycle with mock on-chain state**\n\n```typescript\n// Mock Solana Connection with in-memory account storage\nclass MockConnection {\n  private _slot = 200;\n  private _accounts = new Map<string, { data: Buffer; lamports: number; ... }>();\n  \n  setAccount(pubkey: PublicKey, data: Buffer, opts?: {...}) { ... }\n  async getAccountInfo(pubkey: PublicKey) { ... }\n  async getProgramAccounts(programId: PublicKey, config?: {...}) { ... }\n  async sendRawTransaction(rawTx: Buffer) { ... }\n  async confirmTransaction() { ... }\n}\n\n// Lifecycle: create → watch for join → settle\nit(\"full lifecycle: create → join → settle\", async () => {\n  // 1. Creator calls POST /fairness/coinflip/create\n  const createRes = await app.request(\"/fairness/coinflip/create\", {...});\n  const { matchPda, transaction, commitment } = await createRes.json();\n  \n  // 2. Simulate join on-chain (set account in mock)\n  mockConn.setAccount(matchPdaKey, encodedMatchData);\n  \n  // 3. Settlement worker detects → builds settle tx → submits\n  await settlementWorker.poll();\n  \n  // 4. Verify DB state transitioned: created → locked → settling → settled\n  const round = await db.getRound(matchPda);\n  expect(round.phase).toBe(\"settled\");\n});\n```\n\n**Coverage:**\n- ✅ Create match with proper JWT + amount validation\n- ✅ Detect on-chain match state change\n- ✅ Build settlement transaction\n- ✅ Submit and confirm settlement\n- ✅ Verify database phase transitions\n\n---\n\n#### **F. Event Queue Tests** (`queue.test.ts`, `queue-integration.test.ts`)\n\nPattern: **Database-backed async event system with retries**\n\n**Unit Tests:**\n```typescript\ndescribe(\"emitEvent\", () => {\n  it(\"inserts a row and returns eventId\", async () => {\n    const result = await sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n      return emitEvent(\n        tx,\n        EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED,\n        { referrerWallet: \"abc\", roundId: \"123\" },\n      );\n    });\n    \n    expect(result.eventId).toBeDefined();\n    const rows = await sql`SELECT * FROM event_queue WHERE id = ${result.eventId}`;\n    expect(rows[0]!.status).toBe(\"pending\");\n    expect(rows[0]!.attempts).toBe(0);\n  });\n\n  it(\"does NOT persist when transaction is rolled back\", async () => {\n    let capturedId: bigint | undefined;\n    try {\n      await sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n        const result = await emitEvent(tx, EventTypes.REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED, {...});\n        capturedId = result.eventId;\n        throw new Error(\"rollback\");\n      });\n    } catch { /* expected */ }\n    \n    const rows = await sql`SELECT * FROM event_queue WHERE id = ${capturedId}`;\n    expect(rows).toHaveLength(0);  // Rolled back\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe(\"getBackoffSeconds\", () => {\n  it(\"attempt 1 → 5s, attempt 2 → 30s, attempt 3+ → 300s\", () => {\n    expect(getBackoffSeconds(1)).toBe(5);\n    expect(getBackoffSeconds(2)).toBe(30);\n    expect(getBackoffSeconds(3)).toBe(300);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Integration Tests:**\n```typescript\nit(\"happy path: handler called and event status = completed\", async () => {\n  let handlerCalled = false;\n  registerHandler(EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED, async (payload) => {\n    handlerCalled = true;\n  });\n\n  await sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n    await emitEvent(tx, EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED, { ... });\n  });\n\n  const worker = createEventWorker(sql, { pollIntervalMs: 100 });\n  worker.start();\n  \n  await waitFor(() => handlerCalled, 3000);  // Poll with timeout\n  worker.stop();\n\n  expect(handlerCalled).toBe(true);\n  const rows = await sql`SELECT * FROM event_queue WHERE status = 'completed'`;\n  expect(rows[0]!.completed_at).toBeInstanceOf(Date);\n});\n\nit(\"failure → retry → dead after max_attempts\", async () => {\n  let callCount = 0;\n  registerHandler(EventTypes.REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED, async () => {\n    callCount++;\n    throw new Error(\"failure\");\n  });\n\n  // ... emit event ...\n\n  const worker = createEventWorker(sql);\n  \n  // Attempt 1 — fails, stays pending with backoff\n  await worker.poll();\n  expect(callCount).toBe(1);\n  \n  // Reset scheduled_at for next attempt\n  await sql`UPDATE event_queue SET scheduled_at = now()`;\n  \n  // Attempt 2, 3 — same pattern\n  // After max_attempts: status = 'dead'\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Dependency Mocking Strategy**\n\n| Component | Mock Type | Implementation |\n|-----------|-----------|-----------------|\n| **Solana Connection** | Class-based | `MockConnection` — in-memory accounts, deterministic RPC responses |\n| **Database** | Real Postgres | `postgres@^3.4.0` client, TRUNCATE-based cleanup per test |\n| **JWT Signing** | `jose.SignJWT` | HS256 with test secret, configurable expiration |\n| **Ed25519 Signing** | `tweetnacl.sign.detached` | Real crypto, creates valid signatures for test keypairs |\n| **Keypairs** | `Keypair.generate()` | Real ed25519 keypairs from `@solana/web3.js` |\n| **API Responses** | Hardcoded | Fixed blockhash, slot, balance values |\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Test Helpers & Patterns**\n\n#### **Shared Helpers (Repeated Across Tests)**\n\n```typescript\n// JWT creation\nasync function makeJwt(wallet: string, opts?: { expiresIn?: number }) {\n  const now = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);\n  return new SignJWT({ sub: wallet })\n    .setProtectedHeader({ alg: \"HS256\" })\n    .setIssuedAt(now)\n    .setExpirationTime(now + (opts?.expiresIn ?? 3600))\n    .sign(JWT_SECRET);\n}\n\n// Body builders\nfunction makeBody(wallet: string, overrides?: Partial<{ ... }>) {\n  return {\n    wallet,\n    amountLamports: 5_000_000,\n    side: 0,\n    ...overrides,\n  };\n}\n\n// App builders\nfunction buildApp(opts?: { perWallet?: number; global?: number }) {\n  const app = new Hono();\n  app.use(\"/fairness/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({...}));\n  app.use(\"/fairness/*\", createRateLimitMiddleware({...}));\n  app.route(\"/fairness/coinflip\", createCoinflipRoutes({...}));\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n#### **Database Cleanup Pattern**\n\n```typescript\nbeforeEach(async () => {\n  await rawSql`TRUNCATE rounds, operator_events RESTART IDENTITY`;\n});\n```\n\nSequential file execution + truncate ensures no race conditions.\n\n#### **Polling Helper**\n\n```typescript\nasync function waitFor(\n  condition: () => boolean,\n  timeoutMs: number,\n): Promise<void> {\n  const start = Date.now();\n  while (!condition()) {\n    if (Date.now() - start > timeoutMs) {\n      throw new Error(`waitFor timed out after ${timeoutMs}ms`);\n    }\n    await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 50));\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Key Conventions & Design Patterns**\n\n| Pattern | Usage | Example |\n|---------|-------|---------|\n| **Type casting for JSON** | Safety + explicitness | `const json = (await res.json()) as Record<string, unknown>;` |\n| **Keypair + PublicKey** | Real crypto, deterministic | `creatorKeypair.publicKey.toBase58()` |\n| **Mock account setup** | Simulate on-chain state | `mockConn.setAccount(pda, data, { owner: programId })` |\n| **Database transactions** | Atomicity + rollback testing | `await sql.begin(async (tx) => { ... })` |\n| **Handler registry** | Async event processing | `registerHandler(EventType, async (payload) => {...})` |\n| **SKIP LOCKED polling** | Concurrent safety | Implicit in queue worker design |\n| **Deterministic blockhashes** | Reproducible tests | Same `EETubP5AKHgjPAhzPkA6E6knR1eLPYkevFhfMsaS8CgZ` in all tests |\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Notable Testing Conventions**\n\n✅ **Database-backed tests are sequential** (vitest `fileParallelism: false`)  \n✅ **Each test file is self-contained** (creates app/db in beforeAll, tears down in afterAll)  \n✅ **No mocking of HTTP libraries** — uses Hono's native `.request()` method  \n✅ **No external test fixtures** — all data generated in-test  \n✅ **Real Postgres** — integration tests hit actual database (not sqlite or in-memory)  \n✅ **Crypto is real** — Ed25519 and SHA256 use actual implementations, not mocks  \n✅ **Typed JSON responses** — explicit `as Record<string, unknown>` casting  \n✅ **Clear assertion messages** — use descriptive test names + focused expectations  \n\n---\n\n### 8. **Files & Paths (Absolute)**\n\n```\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/\n├── vitest.config.ts                          # Vitest config (fileParallelism: false)\n├── package.json                              # pnpm test, dependencies\n├── tsconfig.json                             # Node.js target\n├── src/\n│   ├── middleware/\n│   │   ├── jwt-auth.ts                       # Tested in auth.test.ts\n│   │   ├── rate-limit.ts                     # Tested in rate-limit.test.ts\n│   │   └── auth.ts\n│   ├── routes/\n│   │   ├── create.ts                         # Tested in endpoints.test.ts, integration.test.ts\n│   │   ├── lord-create.ts\n│   │   ├── rounds.ts\n│   │   ├── health.ts\n│   │   ├── auth.ts                           # Tested in auth-routes.test.ts\n│   │   └── ...\n│   ├── db.ts                                 # Database types/client\n│   ├── fairness.ts                           # Tested in fairness.test.ts\n│   ├── worker/\n│   │   ├── settlement.js                     # Settlement worker (tested in integration.test.ts)\n│   │   ├── settle-tx.ts\n│   │   └── ...\n│   ├── queue/\n│   │   ├── emit-event.ts                     # Tested in queue.test.ts\n│   │   ├── handler-registry.ts\n│   │   ├── worker.ts                         # Tested in queue-integration.test.ts\n│   │   └── __tests__/\n│   │       ├── queue.test.ts\n│   │       └── queue-integration.test.ts\n│   └── __tests__/\n│       ├── endpoints.test.ts                 # Full stack: middleware + routes + db\n│       ├── auth-routes.test.ts               # Auth lifecycle\n│       ├── auth.test.ts                      # JWT middleware unit\n│       ├── rate-limit.test.ts                # Rate limiter unit\n│       ├── fairness.test.ts                  # Fairness utils unit\n│       └── integration.test.ts               # Full lifecycle create→settle\n```\n\n---\n\nThis test structure provides **comprehensive coverage** from **unit → integration → E2E** with real database integration, proper async handling, and explicit dependency mocking. All tests are deterministic and require only a Postgres database connection (no external services)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a4e1161baf91f9d6f (use SendMessage with to: 'a4e1161baf91f9d6f' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 60821\ntool_uses: 17\nduration_ms: 90091</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aa0285d4-bc35-4024-8afc-77d99fd4e541","uuid":"306c7975-aebc-4dae-b96d-d6c84c25d3de","timestamp":"2026-03-25T13:45:43.193Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and analyze the existing backend test files in sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/. I need to understand:\n1. What test files exist and their patterns (especially endpoint/route tests)\n2. How tests are structured (framework, mocking, setup/teardown)\n3. The test runner configuration (vitest, jest, mocha?)\n4. How route tests mock dependencies (db, config, etc.)\n5. Look specifically at any existing endpoint tests like `endpoints.test.ts`\n\nRead the most relevant test files fully. Be thorough.","agentId":"a4e1161baf91f9d6f","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive view of the backend test structure. Let me create a detailed analysis report.\n\n## Backend Test Files Analysis Report\n\nI've completed a thorough analysis of the backend test infrastructure in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/`. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Test Files Overview**\n\nThe backend has **8 test files** organized by functionality:\n\n| File | Purpose | Lines |\n|------|---------|-------|\n| `src/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` | Full HTTP endpoint stack (middleware + routes) | 451 |\n| `src/__tests__/auth-routes.test.ts` | Auth flow (challenge → verify → refresh → logout) | 298 |\n| `src/__tests__/auth.test.ts` | JWT middleware unit tests | 103 |\n| `src/__tests__/rate-limit.test.ts` | Rate limiter middleware unit tests | 88 |\n| `src/__tests__/fairness.test.ts` | Fairness utility functions (secrets, commitments, PDAs) | 121 |\n| `src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` | Full lifecycle (create → join → settle) | 200+ |\n| `src/queue/__tests__/queue.test.ts` | Event queue unit tests | 157 |\n| `src/queue/__tests__/queue-integration.test.ts` | Event queue worker integration | 150+ |\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Test Framework & Configuration**\n\n**Test Runner:** **Vitest**\n- Configuration file: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/vitest.config.ts`\n- Key setting: `fileParallelism: false` — tests run sequentially to avoid database TRUNCATE races\n\n**Package Manager:** pnpm  \n**Test Command:** `pnpm test` (runs `vitest --passWithNoTests`)\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `vitest@^2.1.0`\n- `postgres@^3.4.0` (database client)\n- `jose@^6.0.0` (JWT signing/verification)\n- `@solana/web3.js@^1.98.0` (keypair/pubkey utilities)\n- `tweetnacl@^1.0.3` (Ed25519 signatures)\n- `bs58@^6.0.0` (base58 encoding/decoding)\n\n**Environment:** Node.js (target: node)\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Testing Architecture Patterns**\n\n#### **A. Middleware Unit Tests** (`auth.test.ts`, `rate-limit.test.ts`)\n\nPattern: **Middleware → Test App → Request → Assert**\n\n```typescript\n// 1. Create a minimal Hono app with the middleware\nfunction createTestApp() {\n  const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();\n  app.use(\"/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: JWT_SECRET }));\n  app.post(\"/test\", (c) => c.json({ ok: true, wallet: c.get(\"wallet\") }));\n  return app;\n}\n\n// 2. Make a request using Hono's built-in request handler\nconst res = await app.request(\"/test\", {\n  method: \"POST\",\n  headers: { \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${token}` },\n  body: JSON.stringify(data),\n});\n\n// 3. Assert response status and JSON\nexpect(res.status).toBe(200);\nconst json = (await res.json()) as Record<string, unknown>;\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Uses **Hono's native `.request()` method** (no external HTTP library)\n- JWT tokens created with `jose.SignJWT`\n- Middleware tested in isolation with minimal dependencies\n- Tests cover both happy paths and edge cases (expired token, wrong secret, missing header)\n\n---\n\n#### **B. Endpoint Tests** (`endpoints.test.ts`)\n\nPattern: **Full middleware stack + routes + database**\n\n```typescript\n// 1. Setup: database + mock connection\nlet db: Db;\nlet mockConn: MockConnection;  // Minimal mock of web3.js Connection\n\nbeforeAll(async () => {\n  db = createDb(DATABASE_URL);  // Real Postgres\n  rawSql = postgres(DATABASE_URL);\n});\n\nbeforeEach(async () => {\n  await rawSql`TRUNCATE rounds, operator_events RESTART IDENTITY`;  // Clean state\n});\n\n// 2. Build app with FULL middleware stack\nfunction buildApp(opts?: { perWallet?: number; global?: number }) {\n  const app = new Hono();\n  \n  // Chain middleware and routes\n  app.use(\"/fairness/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: JWT_SECRET }));\n  app.use(\"/fairness/*\", createRateLimitMiddleware({ ... }));\n  app.route(\"/fairness/coinflip\", createCoinflipRoutes({ db, connection: mockConn, ... }));\n  app.route(\"/fairness/rounds\", createRoundsRoutes({ db }));\n  app.route(\"/health\", createHealthRoutes({ ... }));\n  \n  return app;\n}\n\n// 3. Test scenarios\nit(\"returns 200 with valid JWT\", async () => {\n  const token = await makeJwt(wallet);\n  const res = await app.request(\"/fairness/coinflip/create\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: { \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${token}` },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ wallet, amountLamports: 5_000_000, side: 0 }),\n  });\n  expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n  const json = (await res.json()) as Record<string, unknown>;\n  expect(json.transaction).toBeDefined();\n  expect(json.matchPda).toBeDefined();\n});\n```\n\n**Test Coverage Scope:**\n- ✅ **Auth**: missing JWT (401), expired JWT (401), wallet mismatch (403)\n- ✅ **Rate Limit**: per-wallet limit (429), global limit (429), `Retry-After` header\n- ✅ **Routes**: \n  - `POST /fairness/coinflip/create` — with various JWT states + collision detection\n  - `POST /fairness/lord/create` — valid JWT, response shape\n  - `GET /fairness/rounds/:pda` — known PDA (200), unknown PDA (404)\n  - `GET /health` — status fields, unsettled round count\n- ✅ **Mocking**: Database operations, RPC calls\n\n---\n\n#### **C. Auth Routes Integration Tests** (`auth-routes.test.ts`)\n\nPattern: **Full flow testing with real database**\n\n```typescript\n// Challenge → Sign → Verify → Refresh → Logout → Test Reuse Detection\n\nit(\"full auth flow: challenge → verify → refresh → logout\", async () => {\n  // 1. POST /auth/challenge → get nonce + message\n  const challengeRes = await app.request(\"/auth/challenge\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    body: JSON.stringify({ wallet }),\n  });\n  const { nonce, message } = await challengeRes.json();\n\n  // 2. Sign message with Keypair (nacl.sign.detached)\n  const messageBytes = new TextEncoder().encode(message);\n  const signatureBytes = nacl.sign.detached(messageBytes, creatorKeypair.secretKey);\n  const signature = bs58.encode(signatureBytes);\n\n  // 3. POST /auth/verify → get accessToken + refreshToken\n  const verifyRes = await app.request(\"/auth/verify\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    body: JSON.stringify({ nonce, wallet, signature }),\n  });\n  const tokens = await verifyRes.json();\n  expect(tokens.accessToken).toBeDefined();\n  expect(tokens.refreshToken).toBeDefined();\n\n  // 4. POST /auth/refresh → get new tokens (old token rotated)\n  const refreshRes = await app.request(\"/auth/refresh\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken: tokens.refreshToken }),\n  });\n  const newTokens = await refreshRes.json();\n  expect(newTokens.refreshToken).not.toBe(tokens.refreshToken);  // Rotated\n\n  // 5. Replay old token → fails (401) with \"reuse\" error\n  const replayRes = await app.request(\"/auth/refresh\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken: tokens.refreshToken }),\n  });\n  expect(replayRes.status).toBe(401);\n  expect((await replayRes.json()).error).toContain(\"reuse\");\n\n  // 6. POST /auth/logout → 204\n  const logoutRes = await app.request(\"/auth/logout\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken: newTokens.refreshToken }),\n  });\n  expect(logoutRes.status).toBe(204);\n\n  // 7. POST-logout refresh fails\n  const postLogoutRes = await app.request(\"/auth/refresh\", {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken: newTokens.refreshToken }),\n  });\n  expect(postLogoutRes.status).toBe(401);\n});\n```\n\n**Edge Cases Tested:**\n- ✅ Wrong wallet claim with correct signature (401)\n- ✅ Correct wallet with wrong signature (401)\n- ✅ Nonce reuse prevention\n- ✅ Refresh token rotation\n- ✅ Logout revocation\n\n---\n\n#### **D. Fairness Unit Tests** (`fairness.test.ts`)\n\nPattern: **Pure function unit tests with deterministic checks**\n\n```typescript\ndescribe(\"computeCommitment\", () => {\n  it(\"matches packages/fairness commitment algorithm\", () => {\n    const seedHex = \"abcdef0123456789...\";\n    const seedBytes = Buffer.from(seedHex, \"hex\");\n    \n    const backendCommitment = computeCommitment(seedBytes).toString(\"hex\");\n    \n    // Cross-check with Node crypto for verification\n    const nodeCommitment = createHash(\"sha256\").update(seedBytes).digest(\"hex\");\n    \n    expect(backendCommitment).toBe(nodeCommitment);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe(\"deriveMatchPda\", () => {\n  it(\"matches manual PDA derivation with seeds [match, creator, matchId]\", () => {\n    const matchId = Buffer.from(\"deadbeef01234567\", \"hex\");\n    \n    const [expected] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n      [Buffer.from(\"match\"), creator.toBuffer(), matchId],\n      programId,\n    );\n    \n    const [actual] = deriveMatchPda(creator, matchId);\n    expect(actual.equals(expected)).toBe(true);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Functions Tested:**\n- ✅ `generateSecret()` — 32 bytes, unique per call\n- ✅ `computeCommitment()` — SHA256 determinism, cross-package agreement\n- ✅ `generateMatchId()` — 8 bytes, unique per call\n- ✅ `deriveMatchPda()` — PDA derivation correctness, determinism, different creators/matchIds\n\n---\n\n#### **E. Integration Tests** (`integration.test.ts`)\n\nPattern: **Full lifecycle with mock on-chain state**\n\n```typescript\n// Mock Solana Connection with in-memory account storage\nclass MockConnection {\n  private _slot = 200;\n  private _accounts = new Map<string, { data: Buffer; lamports: number; ... }>();\n  \n  setAccount(pubkey: PublicKey, data: Buffer, opts?: {...}) { ... }\n  async getAccountInfo(pubkey: PublicKey) { ... }\n  async getProgramAccounts(programId: PublicKey, config?: {...}) { ... }\n  async sendRawTransaction(rawTx: Buffer) { ... }\n  async confirmTransaction() { ... }\n}\n\n// Lifecycle: create → watch for join → settle\nit(\"full lifecycle: create → join → settle\", async () => {\n  // 1. Creator calls POST /fairness/coinflip/create\n  const createRes = await app.request(\"/fairness/coinflip/create\", {...});\n  const { matchPda, transaction, commitment } = await createRes.json();\n  \n  // 2. Simulate join on-chain (set account in mock)\n  mockConn.setAccount(matchPdaKey, encodedMatchData);\n  \n  // 3. Settlement worker detects → builds settle tx → submits\n  await settlementWorker.poll();\n  \n  // 4. Verify DB state transitioned: created → locked → settling → settled\n  const round = await db.getRound(matchPda);\n  expect(round.phase).toBe(\"settled\");\n});\n```\n\n**Coverage:**\n- ✅ Create match with proper JWT + amount validation\n- ✅ Detect on-chain match state change\n- ✅ Build settlement transaction\n- ✅ Submit and confirm settlement\n- ✅ Verify database phase transitions\n\n---\n\n#### **F. Event Queue Tests** (`queue.test.ts`, `queue-integration.test.ts`)\n\nPattern: **Database-backed async event system with retries**\n\n**Unit Tests:**\n```typescript\ndescribe(\"emitEvent\", () => {\n  it(\"inserts a row and returns eventId\", async () => {\n    const result = await sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n      return emitEvent(\n        tx,\n        EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED,\n        { referrerWallet: \"abc\", roundId: \"123\" },\n      );\n    });\n    \n    expect(result.eventId).toBeDefined();\n    const rows = await sql`SELECT * FROM event_queue WHERE id = ${result.eventId}`;\n    expect(rows[0]!.status).toBe(\"pending\");\n    expect(rows[0]!.attempts).toBe(0);\n  });\n\n  it(\"does NOT persist when transaction is rolled back\", async () => {\n    let capturedId: bigint | undefined;\n    try {\n      await sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n        const result = await emitEvent(tx, EventTypes.REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED, {...});\n        capturedId = result.eventId;\n        throw new Error(\"rollback\");\n      });\n    } catch { /* expected */ }\n    \n    const rows = await sql`SELECT * FROM event_queue WHERE id = ${capturedId}`;\n    expect(rows).toHaveLength(0);  // Rolled back\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe(\"getBackoffSeconds\", () => {\n  it(\"attempt 1 → 5s, attempt 2 → 30s, attempt 3+ → 300s\", () => {\n    expect(getBackoffSeconds(1)).toBe(5);\n    expect(getBackoffSeconds(2)).toBe(30);\n    expect(getBackoffSeconds(3)).toBe(300);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Integration Tests:**\n```typescript\nit(\"happy path: handler called and event status = completed\", async () => {\n  let handlerCalled = false;\n  registerHandler(EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED, async (payload) => {\n    handlerCalled = true;\n  });\n\n  await sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n    await emitEvent(tx, EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED, { ... });\n  });\n\n  const worker = createEventWorker(sql, { pollIntervalMs: 100 });\n  worker.start();\n  \n  await waitFor(() => handlerCalled, 3000);  // Poll with timeout\n  worker.stop();\n\n  expect(handlerCalled).toBe(true);\n  const rows = await sql`SELECT * FROM event_queue WHERE status = 'completed'`;\n  expect(rows[0]!.completed_at).toBeInstanceOf(Date);\n});\n\nit(\"failure → retry → dead after max_attempts\", async () => {\n  let callCount = 0;\n  registerHandler(EventTypes.REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED, async () => {\n    callCount++;\n    throw new Error(\"failure\");\n  });\n\n  // ... emit event ...\n\n  const worker = createEventWorker(sql);\n  \n  // Attempt 1 — fails, stays pending with backoff\n  await worker.poll();\n  expect(callCount).toBe(1);\n  \n  // Reset scheduled_at for next attempt\n  await sql`UPDATE event_queue SET scheduled_at = now()`;\n  \n  // Attempt 2, 3 — same pattern\n  // After max_attempts: status = 'dead'\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Dependency Mocking Strategy**\n\n| Component | Mock Type | Implementation |\n|-----------|-----------|-----------------|\n| **Solana Connection** | Class-based | `MockConnection` — in-memory accounts, deterministic RPC responses |\n| **Database** | Real Postgres | `postgres@^3.4.0` client, TRUNCATE-based cleanup per test |\n| **JWT Signing** | `jose.SignJWT` | HS256 with test secret, configurable expiration |\n| **Ed25519 Signing** | `tweetnacl.sign.detached` | Real crypto, creates valid signatures for test keypairs |\n| **Keypairs** | `Keypair.generate()` | Real ed25519 keypairs from `@solana/web3.js` |\n| **API Responses** | Hardcoded | Fixed blockhash, slot, balance values |\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Test Helpers & Patterns**\n\n#### **Shared Helpers (Repeated Across Tests)**\n\n```typescript\n// JWT creation\nasync function makeJwt(wallet: string, opts?: { expiresIn?: number }) {\n  const now = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);\n  return new SignJWT({ sub: wallet })\n    .setProtectedHeader({ alg: \"HS256\" })\n    .setIssuedAt(now)\n    .setExpirationTime(now + (opts?.expiresIn ?? 3600))\n    .sign(JWT_SECRET);\n}\n\n// Body builders\nfunction makeBody(wallet: string, overrides?: Partial<{ ... }>) {\n  return {\n    wallet,\n    amountLamports: 5_000_000,\n    side: 0,\n    ...overrides,\n  };\n}\n\n// App builders\nfunction buildApp(opts?: { perWallet?: number; global?: number }) {\n  const app = new Hono();\n  app.use(\"/fairness/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({...}));\n  app.use(\"/fairness/*\", createRateLimitMiddleware({...}));\n  app.route(\"/fairness/coinflip\", createCoinflipRoutes({...}));\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n#### **Database Cleanup Pattern**\n\n```typescript\nbeforeEach(async () => {\n  await rawSql`TRUNCATE rounds, operator_events RESTART IDENTITY`;\n});\n```\n\nSequential file execution + truncate ensures no race conditions.\n\n#### **Polling Helper**\n\n```typescript\nasync function waitFor(\n  condition: () => boolean,\n  timeoutMs: number,\n): Promise<void> {\n  const start = Date.now();\n  while (!condition()) {\n    if (Date.now() - start > timeoutMs) {\n      throw new Error(`waitFor timed out after ${timeoutMs}ms`);\n    }\n    await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 50));\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Key Conventions & Design Patterns**\n\n| Pattern | Usage | Example |\n|---------|-------|---------|\n| **Type casting for JSON** | Safety + explicitness | `const json = (await res.json()) as Record<string, unknown>;` |\n| **Keypair + PublicKey** | Real crypto, deterministic | `creatorKeypair.publicKey.toBase58()` |\n| **Mock account setup** | Simulate on-chain state | `mockConn.setAccount(pda, data, { owner: programId })` |\n| **Database transactions** | Atomicity + rollback testing | `await sql.begin(async (tx) => { ... })` |\n| **Handler registry** | Async event processing | `registerHandler(EventType, async (payload) => {...})` |\n| **SKIP LOCKED polling** | Concurrent safety | Implicit in queue worker design |\n| **Deterministic blockhashes** | Reproducible tests | Same `EETubP5AKHgjPAhzPkA6E6knR1eLPYkevFhfMsaS8CgZ` in all tests |\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Notable Testing Conventions**\n\n✅ **Database-backed tests are sequential** (vitest `fileParallelism: false`)  \n✅ **Each test file is self-contained** (creates app/db in beforeAll, tears down in afterAll)  \n✅ **No mocking of HTTP libraries** — uses Hono's native `.request()` method  \n✅ **No external test fixtures** — all data generated in-test  \n✅ **Real Postgres** — integration tests hit actual database (not sqlite or in-memory)  \n✅ **Crypto is real** — Ed25519 and SHA256 use actual implementations, not mocks  \n✅ **Typed JSON responses** — explicit `as Record<string, unknown>` casting  \n✅ **Clear assertion messages** — use descriptive test names + focused expectations  \n\n---\n\n### 8. **Files & Paths (Absolute)**\n\n```\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/\n├── vitest.config.ts                          # Vitest config (fileParallelism: false)\n├── package.json                              # pnpm test, dependencies\n├── tsconfig.json                             # Node.js target\n├── src/\n│   ├── middleware/\n│   │   ├── jwt-auth.ts                       # Tested in auth.test.ts\n│   │   ├── rate-limit.ts                     # Tested in rate-limit.test.ts\n│   │   └── auth.ts\n│   ├── routes/\n│   │   ├── create.ts                         # Tested in endpoints.test.ts, integration.test.ts\n│   │   ├── lord-create.ts\n│   │   ├── rounds.ts\n│   │   ├── health.ts\n│   │   ├── auth.ts                           # Tested in auth-routes.test.ts\n│   │   └── ...\n│   ├── db.ts                                 # Database types/client\n│   ├── fairness.ts                           # Tested in fairness.test.ts\n│   ├── worker/\n│   │   ├── settlement.js                     # Settlement worker (tested in integration.test.ts)\n│   │   ├── settle-tx.ts\n│   │   └── ...\n│   ├── queue/\n│   │   ├── emit-event.ts                     # Tested in queue.test.ts\n│   │   ├── handler-registry.ts\n│   │   ├── worker.ts                         # Tested in queue-integration.test.ts\n│   │   └── __tests__/\n│   │       ├── queue.test.ts\n│   │       └── queue-integration.test.ts\n│   └── __tests__/\n│       ├── endpoints.test.ts                 # Full stack: middleware + routes + db\n│       ├── auth-routes.test.ts               # Auth lifecycle\n│       ├── auth.test.ts                      # JWT middleware unit\n│       ├── rate-limit.test.ts                # Rate limiter unit\n│       ├── fairness.test.ts                  # Fairness utils unit\n│       └── integration.test.ts               # Full lifecycle create→settle\n```\n\n---\n\nThis test structure provides **comprehensive coverage** from **unit → integration → E2E** with real database integration, proper async handling, and explicit dependency mocking. All tests are deterministic and require only a Postgres database connection (no external services)."}],"totalDurationMs":90091,"totalTo